387
00:23:44,680 --> 00:23:45,960
Jean.

388
00:23:46,040 --> 00:23:50,760
Who won the "Up, Up, Clear Away"
master class?

389
00:23:53,480 --> 00:23:54,360
Peem.

390
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:03,800
We just went wild. Hugging and screaming.

391
00:24:03,880 --> 00:24:07,040
We would've tossed Peem in the air.
The energy was amazing.

392
00:24:07,120 --> 00:24:11,280
<i>The Face Men </i>brotherhood is so strong.
I'm thrilled.

393
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:14,840
I felt like I was glowing…

394
00:24:16,640 --> 00:24:19,480
This is what seven episodes
of pent-up stress look like.

395
00:24:19,560 --> 00:24:22,240
I was so stressed,
but today I'm finally clear.

396
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:24,560
Thank you all for today.

397
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:27,320
For joining our
"Up, Up, Clear Away" master class.

398
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:29,120
Thank you so much, Jean.

399
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:30,520
Thank you, Sabina.

400
00:24:30,600 --> 00:24:32,120
And thank you, Ice Paris.

401
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:35,040
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

402
00:24:35,120 --> 00:24:38,480
You still have one hurdle left.

403
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:41,040
We have to wait and see what it is.

404
00:24:45,320 --> 00:24:47,480
I'm expecting to win this campaign.

405
00:24:47,560 --> 00:24:48,920
I really want a win.

406
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:52,120
I want the boys to feel
the pride they deserve.

407
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:53,520
We're going all in.

408
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:55,720
My boys were born fighters.

409
00:24:55,800 --> 00:24:57,880
I've also been doing my homework.

410
00:24:57,960 --> 00:25:01,920
I just hope the boys channel
some kind of spirit today.

411
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:04,840
Just not the same messy vibe as before.

412
00:25:04,920 --> 00:25:09,120
I need to go light some incense
and pray for a good one.

413
00:26:05,840 --> 00:26:08,560
The final campaign
before the Selection round.

414
00:26:08,640 --> 00:26:10,560
I hope today is my day.

415
00:26:11,280 --> 00:26:14,840
I'm going all in for this last campaign.
Let's see what happens.

416
00:26:14,920 --> 00:26:15,880
Hi, everyone.

417
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:17,040
- Hello.
- Hello.

418
00:26:17,120 --> 00:26:20,040
Welcome to our campaign today.

419
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:23,480
Today's theme
is still "Up, Up, Clear Away."

420
00:26:23,560 --> 00:26:26,720
Let's meet the person
giving us today's brief.

421
00:26:26,800 --> 00:26:30,360
Give it up for Sophon Kaethong,

422
00:26:30,440 --> 00:26:35,040
Media and Digital Marketing Lead,
Beauty and Wellbeing, Unilever Thailand.

423
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:36,200
Also known as Golf.

424
00:26:39,680 --> 00:26:43,440
SOPHON KAETHONG

425
00:26:43,520 --> 00:26:47,200
In the master class, you guys shot
an MV for the song "Is that CLEAR?"

426
00:26:47,280 --> 00:26:50,840
You've already filmed the singing parts.
Today, we're shooting the rest.

427
00:26:50,920 --> 00:26:53,120
To make this MV absolutely perfect,

428
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:55,000
what you all will be filming today

429
00:26:55,080 --> 00:26:58,720
is the part that makes this MV fun,
vibrant, and engaging.

430
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:02,280
It's the choreography
that you've all been practicing.

431
00:27:02,360 --> 00:27:05,800
Let's see my smooth moves.
Don't stop me, because I'm unstoppable.

432
00:27:05,880 --> 00:27:08,920
Ready to give my all,
because I've got Clear.

433
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:10,760
We continue from the master class.

434
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:13,000
After waking up, showering,
and dressing up,

435
00:27:13,080 --> 00:27:15,360
you prep your hair
with Clear Ice Cool Menthol.

436
00:27:15,440 --> 00:27:18,000
Leaving your hair and scalp
feeling totally refreshed.

437
00:27:18,080 --> 00:27:21,840
You'll hold a giant balloon,
floating down from the floating house,

438
00:27:21,920 --> 00:27:23,680
landing straight into your dance,

439
00:27:23,760 --> 00:27:29,440
transitioning through backgrounds,
from extreme heat to freezing cold.

440
00:27:29,520 --> 00:27:31,600
And of course, no matter the weather,

441
00:27:31,680 --> 00:27:34,080
nothing will stop you
from finding true love.

442
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:36,400
I want to see everyone
dance with confidence,

443
00:27:36,480 --> 00:27:38,640
and conquer any weather condition.

444
00:27:38,720 --> 00:27:41,360
There will also be a freestyle segment.

445
00:27:41,440 --> 00:27:45,280
This is your chance to show off
your skills, bring out your star quality,

446
00:27:45,360 --> 00:27:48,200
and turn this music video
into a total masterpiece.

447
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:50,720
The real challenge of this campaign

448
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:53,080
isn't just for each contestant.

449
00:27:53,160 --> 00:27:54,800
It's also on our mentors.

450
00:27:54,880 --> 00:27:57,320
We want to see how each of you
creates and designs

451
00:27:57,400 --> 00:28:00,280
the freestyle and choreography sections.

452
00:28:00,360 --> 00:28:03,600
For me, the freestyle part
will be very challenging.

453
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:05,120
I think it's the hardest part.

454
00:28:05,200 --> 00:28:07,240
My vision for today is crystal clear.

455
00:28:07,320 --> 00:28:08,880
I'll float down, bam.

456
00:28:08,960 --> 00:28:10,880
I dance with total confidence.

457
00:28:12,040 --> 00:28:14,640
Golf, what kind of dancing do you expect

458
00:28:14,720 --> 00:28:17,560
that best captures the ultimate Clear Man?

459
00:28:17,640 --> 00:28:19,200
Well, to be a Clear Man,

460
00:28:19,280 --> 00:28:23,520
first, you need to clear
all the worries from your head.

461
00:28:23,600 --> 00:28:27,080
The character of a Clear Man
is someone with an active lifestyle.

462
00:28:27,160 --> 00:28:28,400
He loves being outdoors.

463
00:28:28,480 --> 00:28:31,200
When he's out being active,
he goes all out.

464
00:28:31,280 --> 00:28:33,120
When he comes home and uses Clear,

465
00:28:33,200 --> 00:28:35,640
he stays clean and fresh.

466
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:38,800
He feels totally refreshed
and completely dandruff-free.

467
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:42,600
So a Clear Man always has to feel fresh.

468
00:28:42,680 --> 00:28:46,400
It gives him the confidence
to clear the air with the one he loves.

469
00:28:46,480 --> 00:28:48,760
I want you all
to dance with total confidence

470
00:28:48,840 --> 00:28:51,320
and stand out enough to win this campaign.

471
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:52,840
This campaign has a song,

472
00:28:52,920 --> 00:28:55,400
so I will feel it in my soul

473
00:28:55,480 --> 00:28:58,200
and let the rhythm
take over my lower body.

474
00:28:59,000 --> 00:29:01,440
Dance. Just pure dancing.

475
00:29:01,520 --> 00:29:04,400
Let me explain the rules

476
00:29:04,480 --> 00:29:07,200
for the "Up, Up, Clear Away" campaign.

477
00:29:07,280 --> 00:29:10,760
Each team will have time
to ask our Clear client questions.

478
00:29:10,840 --> 00:29:12,080
Five minutes per team.

479
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:16,560
After that, you get 25 minutes
to rehearse on set.

480
00:29:16,640 --> 00:29:19,240
Each team will have time
to shoot the scene

481
00:29:19,320 --> 00:29:23,120
jumping out of the sky house
with the Clear balloons.

482
00:29:23,200 --> 00:29:25,120
Just five minutes per team.

483
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:26,080
After that,

484
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:30,200
each team will have 15 minutes
to shoot the hook.

485
00:29:30,280 --> 00:29:32,880
The other teams must join the performance.

486
00:29:32,960 --> 00:29:36,200
But the competing team must be
the absolute center of attention.

487
00:29:36,280 --> 00:29:40,360
Then all teams will shoot
the freestyle segment together.

488
00:29:40,440 --> 00:29:43,920
And you only get one take per team.

489
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:46,840
For today's winning team,

490
00:29:46,920 --> 00:29:50,680
the mentor can pick one extra contestant

491
00:29:50,760 --> 00:29:52,800
to join the Final Walk.

492
00:29:52,880 --> 00:29:55,120
My mentor doesn't have to stress at all.

493
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:57,920
Because I'm the only one left.
No choosing required.

494
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:01,680
If the winner of this campaign gets
to take two people to the Final Walk,

495
00:30:01,760 --> 00:30:03,600
but his team is down to one person,

496
00:30:03,680 --> 00:30:07,760
I'm not sure whether the prize changes,
or whether they can bring someone back.

497
00:30:07,840 --> 00:30:11,600
Peem, you won the last master class.

498
00:30:11,680 --> 00:30:13,040
Step forward, please.

499
00:30:13,120 --> 00:30:16,120
Do you think you can lead Team Mile

500
00:30:16,200 --> 00:30:18,440
to win both the master class
and the campaign?

501
00:30:18,520 --> 00:30:19,520
Absolutely.

502
00:30:20,240 --> 00:30:23,360
- We're moving as a team today.
- Why are you so confident?

503
00:30:23,440 --> 00:30:25,560
Because I use Clear every day.

504
00:30:27,640 --> 00:30:30,720
After winning the master class,
I got an additional privilege.

505
00:30:30,800 --> 00:30:33,960
That's why everyone
is being nice to me today.

506
00:30:34,040 --> 00:30:36,160
As the winner of the master class,

507
00:30:36,240 --> 00:30:39,840
you get to choose the performance order.

508
00:30:39,920 --> 00:30:40,920
So, Peem.

509
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:43,720
Which order do you want for your team?

510
00:30:48,040 --> 00:30:51,600
Team Mile will be
the second team to perform.

511
00:30:51,680 --> 00:30:54,040
We have to dance for the other teams too.

512
00:30:54,120 --> 00:30:56,840
That means we'll need a lot of energy.

513
00:30:56,920 --> 00:30:58,960
Going second will give us an advantage.

514
00:30:59,040 --> 00:31:02,080
Which team do you want to go first?

515
00:31:02,920 --> 00:31:05,400
- Don't look at me.
- I'm avoiding it.

516
00:31:05,480 --> 00:31:07,520
- Say it to my face.
- I avoid eye contact.

517
00:31:07,600 --> 00:31:09,840
Let's hold hands first.
Come on, hold my hand.

518
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:12,240
Hey, hold my hand too.

519
00:31:12,840 --> 00:31:15,080
Hold mine. I'm solo,
and you leave me hanging?

520
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:16,600
Let's put Team Off first.

521
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:18,080
- Okay.
- Right.

522
00:31:18,160 --> 00:31:20,200
- And Kimhan's team goes last.
- Okay.

523
00:31:20,280 --> 00:31:23,960
Let me summarize
today's performance order.

524
00:31:24,040 --> 00:31:27,400
Up first is Team Off.

525
00:31:27,480 --> 00:31:29,960
Your setting will be the ice scene.

526
00:31:30,040 --> 00:31:33,280
Going first is fine.
We get to set the bar and intimidate them.

527
00:31:33,360 --> 00:31:36,000
If we crush it, don't act surprised.

528
00:31:36,080 --> 00:31:39,320
Going second is Team Mile.

529
00:31:39,400 --> 00:31:41,600
Your setting will be the meadow.

530
00:31:41,680 --> 00:31:44,400
It was our choice. We wanted to go second.

531
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:48,520
I'm confident. It's the sweet spot.
Not too exhausting either way.

532
00:31:48,600 --> 00:31:51,920
Our final team is Team Pancake-Ananda.

533
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:54,600
Your setting will be the desert.

534
00:31:54,680 --> 00:31:58,840
I won't get exhausted, save my energy.
Let the others dance themselves out.

535
00:31:58,920 --> 00:32:00,120
I just feel bad for him.

536
00:32:00,200 --> 00:32:02,440
He's the last one,
and I'm the first to dance.

537
00:32:03,440 --> 00:32:05,120
Will anyone even care
to watch him after me?

538
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:08,480
Now that we know
the performance order and the rules,

539
00:32:08,560 --> 00:32:10,640
everyone, please go get ready.

540
00:32:13,480 --> 00:32:17,960
We're going to win this.
Two of us are going to the Final Walk.

541
00:32:18,040 --> 00:32:19,640
- Hello.
- Hello.

542
00:32:19,720 --> 00:32:21,840
- Maybe I'll ask later.
- Take your time.

543
00:32:21,920 --> 00:32:23,080
Does my shirt blend in?

544
00:32:23,160 --> 00:32:25,560
Today's brief is "Up, Up, Clear Away".

545
00:32:25,640 --> 00:32:29,040
We already shot the singing portions
during the master class.

546
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:31,800
For this campaign,
we're shooting the choreography.

547
00:32:31,880 --> 00:32:33,760
Based on the last master class,

548
00:32:33,840 --> 00:32:37,560
Golf, is there anything you want
Team Off to change?

549
00:32:37,640 --> 00:32:39,640
I want them to focus on the story.

550
00:32:39,720 --> 00:32:42,520
Bonus, for example.
He always gives all his energy.

551
00:32:42,600 --> 00:32:46,320
But we can't tell
if there's an actual story behind it.

552
00:32:46,400 --> 00:32:48,000
I want to see more storytelling.

553
00:32:48,080 --> 00:32:49,720
I need to believe in his acting.

554
00:32:49,800 --> 00:32:52,280
He needs to interpret
the song and convey that,

555
00:32:52,360 --> 00:32:55,000
rather than just treating it
like a fun dance routine.

556
00:32:55,080 --> 00:32:56,720
- And Pom?
- I liked Pom's opening.

557
00:32:56,800 --> 00:33:01,000
He understood the song, but lost focus.
He struggled to stay in character.

558
00:33:01,960 --> 00:33:03,440
As for Rome…

559
00:33:03,520 --> 00:33:06,440
It seems like he's not so comfortable
in his own body.

560
00:33:06,520 --> 00:33:09,680
We aren't just judging the dancing.
It's not about choreography.

561
00:33:09,760 --> 00:33:10,840
We don't want dancers.

562
00:33:10,920 --> 00:33:13,160
- Okay.
- Just someone to represent the brand

563
00:33:13,240 --> 00:33:15,760
and express what we're looking for.

564
00:33:15,840 --> 00:33:18,520
We want to see confidence and fun.

565
00:33:18,600 --> 00:33:22,280
My team is arguably
the weakest at dancing.

566
00:33:22,360 --> 00:33:25,320
If we're talking about fun and confidence…

567
00:33:25,400 --> 00:33:28,880
- My boys can handle this.
- We're not judging solely on the dancing.

568
00:33:28,960 --> 00:33:31,080
- Perfect.
- I want them to have fun.

569
00:33:31,160 --> 00:33:34,080
If Clear were an artist…

570
00:33:34,160 --> 00:33:37,280
We picture BTS. Like…

571
00:33:37,360 --> 00:33:40,960
I just cut the team down to seven,
the same number as BTS.

572
00:33:41,040 --> 00:33:42,400
They want a boy group.

573
00:33:42,480 --> 00:33:45,880
Our team is down to seven guys.

574
00:33:45,960 --> 00:33:47,640
We are one team.

575
00:33:47,720 --> 00:33:49,520
We are TFM.

576
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:51,160
- Hi.
- Hi.

577
00:33:51,240 --> 00:33:54,120
I just want to check out the set first.

578
00:33:54,200 --> 00:33:56,080
Excuse me. Pardon me.

579
00:33:56,160 --> 00:33:59,760
Before I ask my questions,
I want to make sure my boys will be safe.

580
00:33:59,840 --> 00:34:03,720
I'm jumping around,
imagining how it will look.

581
00:34:03,800 --> 00:34:06,720
It's fun just randomly
jumping around <i>The Face </i>set.

582
00:34:06,800 --> 00:34:09,760
What mood and tone are you looking for?

583
00:34:09,840 --> 00:34:12,679
- Honestly, this is a really fun track.
- Right.

584
00:34:12,760 --> 00:34:16,360
I want them to feel confident
and have fun above all else.

585
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:19,440
Second, they need to interpret the song.

586
00:34:19,520 --> 00:34:20,920
- Since you're a team…
- Yes.

587
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:23,239
Everyone needs to be on the same page.

588
00:34:23,320 --> 00:34:26,880
So the balloon represents
happiness and confidence.

589
00:34:26,960 --> 00:34:28,960
- Exactly.
- Finding love, finally.

590
00:34:29,040 --> 00:34:30,360
Their crush.

591
00:34:30,440 --> 00:34:32,520
Their crush? Okay, got it.

592
00:34:32,600 --> 00:34:34,960
Does the product need to be in the hook?

593
00:34:35,040 --> 00:34:36,199
- No need.
- No need.

594
00:34:36,280 --> 00:34:37,760
- Just wondering.
- Yes?

595
00:34:37,840 --> 00:34:42,159
For the camera angles I want,
I'll need a tall ladder.

596
00:34:42,239 --> 00:34:44,880
- Like a Gen Z vibe, you know?
- Absolutely.

597
00:34:44,960 --> 00:34:46,440
Go wild with your creativity.

598
00:34:46,520 --> 00:34:49,280
Anything specific you want
for the meadow scene?

599
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:52,679
The meadow represents
comfort, freshness, and cleanliness.

600
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:54,400
It perfectly matches our product.

601
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:55,960
- Freedom.
- Exactly.

602
00:34:56,040 --> 00:34:59,160
What does the client's ideal
love interest look like?

603
00:34:59,240 --> 00:35:02,120
Everyone has their own type.

604
00:35:02,200 --> 00:35:04,840
Just imagine whoever you're searching for.

605
00:35:04,920 --> 00:35:06,800
- Thanks. That covers everything.
- Okay.

606
00:35:06,880 --> 00:35:09,600
I truly believe in the "flow state."

607
00:35:09,680 --> 00:35:12,320
It's when your mind is completely clear.

608
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:15,080
You just want to explore everything.

609
00:35:15,160 --> 00:35:17,400
Clear is what brings us
into that flow state.

610
00:35:17,480 --> 00:35:18,960
- Hi.
- Hi.

611
00:35:19,040 --> 00:35:21,880
- So glad to see you again.
- Great to see you too.

612
00:35:21,960 --> 00:35:25,560
Is the vibe more like a music video
or a fashion music video?

613
00:35:25,640 --> 00:35:26,600
It's a music video.

614
00:35:26,680 --> 00:35:28,120
- A music video. Okay.
- Right.

615
00:35:28,200 --> 00:35:31,640
There are many dance parts
in the music video.

616
00:35:31,720 --> 00:35:34,680
Which parts will actually
make it into the final cut?

617
00:35:34,760 --> 00:35:38,320
There will be two main parts. The first is
the group dance during the hook.

618
00:35:38,400 --> 00:35:40,840
- Right.
- Every team does the same choreography.

619
00:35:40,920 --> 00:35:42,760
- But with different backdrops.
- Right.

620
00:35:42,840 --> 00:35:46,960
- Your team also needs to improvise.
- Okay.

621
00:35:47,040 --> 00:35:50,360
I want a storyline
where they're hanging out and dancing.

622
00:35:50,440 --> 00:35:51,880
- Or some interaction.
- Got it.

623
00:35:51,960 --> 00:35:54,640
Make the song interesting.
Don't dance the whole time.

624
00:35:54,720 --> 00:35:57,840
We need some cuts
where they play with the camera.

625
00:35:57,920 --> 00:35:59,200
- Or interact.
- Got it.

626
00:35:59,280 --> 00:36:01,440
I want to see chemistry between teammates

627
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:04,880
and the rest,
not just hanging out and having fun.

628
00:36:04,960 --> 00:36:07,760
My boy can really stand out
since he's the only one left.

629
00:36:07,840 --> 00:36:09,120
Fair enough.

630
00:36:10,040 --> 00:36:13,040
Any specific shots you want to highlight?

631
00:36:13,120 --> 00:36:16,560
Definitely the dance shots.
They're the main highlight.

632
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:18,280
- The hook?
- Exactly, the hook.

633
00:36:18,360 --> 00:36:19,320
Okay.

634
00:36:19,400 --> 00:36:22,000
Kimhan has to nail this
and bring out that inner fire.

635
00:36:22,080 --> 00:36:27,120
Show them you really get the vibe.
It's about whoever wins the client over.

636
00:36:27,200 --> 00:36:30,440
- Let's go, guys. Time to learn the choreo.
- To this song?

637
00:36:30,520 --> 00:36:33,920
I feel like this campaign is tough
because we actually have to do it.

638
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:36,480
I never thought
I would be learning choreography.

639
00:36:36,560 --> 00:36:38,600
Stop, got it?

640
00:36:38,680 --> 00:36:40,720
- One more time. Six…
- I think I got it.

641
00:36:40,800 --> 00:36:45,200
Clear, clear, slide, clear. And you?

642
00:36:45,280 --> 00:36:47,640
- There's a rhythm to it… "And you."
- Oh, got it.

643
00:36:47,720 --> 00:36:49,200
- I see.
- "And you."

644
00:36:49,280 --> 00:36:50,520
- It's a dance song.
- Yes.

645
00:36:50,600 --> 00:36:52,040
Saying that feels like a threat.

646
00:36:52,120 --> 00:36:53,040
Let's go again.

647
00:36:53,120 --> 00:36:56,320
When I dance, I'm analyzing
the footwork and the rhythm.

648
00:36:56,400 --> 00:37:00,080
So when it's time to shoot,
I can spot if they mess up a step.

649
00:37:00,160 --> 00:37:04,640
- I'm clear, clear, clear, and you?
- Clear, clear, clear, and you?

650
00:37:04,720 --> 00:37:06,600
- Wait, that's… "and clear."
- And clear.

651
00:37:06,680 --> 00:37:09,680
Clear, clear, clear. I'm literally
going to dream about this.

652
00:37:09,760 --> 00:37:10,640
- Pan,
- What?

653
00:37:10,720 --> 00:37:14,160
- How'd you do the joyful <i>Kinnaree </i>pose?
- The joyful <i>Kinnaree </i>in the water.

654
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:16,480
- Rising up to see a wet bear…
- Yes?

655
00:37:16,560 --> 00:37:17,440
Or whatever it is.

656
00:37:17,520 --> 00:37:21,800
Looks like Pan is more of an expert
at the joyful <i>Kinnaree</i>.

657
00:37:24,480 --> 00:37:25,520
I have no idea how.

658
00:37:25,600 --> 00:37:27,840
I'll just let everyone see what it is.

659
00:37:27,920 --> 00:37:29,760
All right, everyone.

660
00:37:29,840 --> 00:37:34,280
So the plan is
that the seven of us are now one team.

661
00:37:34,360 --> 00:37:35,800
Our boy band is called TFM.

662
00:37:36,400 --> 00:37:38,960
Let's dial up the characters again.

663
00:37:39,040 --> 00:37:41,240
You're charismatic, the all-rounder.

664
00:37:41,320 --> 00:37:44,360
Manyoo, you are the cool, sporty guy.

665
00:37:44,960 --> 00:37:49,080
Next is Bonus, the edgy guy.
Ready for anything, totally sincere.

666
00:37:49,920 --> 00:37:52,280
Rome. Shy, affectionate. Little kitten.

667
00:37:52,360 --> 00:37:56,520
I don't think it's hard.
I can pull this off. I'll nail it.

668
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:01,400
Gluf, the bright, fresh-faced youngest.

669
00:38:01,480 --> 00:38:04,480
Kimhan, our strong leader.

670
00:38:04,560 --> 00:38:07,760
Peem, main dancer.
Every move you make sets the standard.

671
00:38:07,840 --> 00:38:09,840
See that? How was it?

672
00:38:09,920 --> 00:38:13,200
We assigned roles to everyone
and mapped out their vibe.

673
00:38:13,280 --> 00:38:15,840
And honestly, the characters we gave them?

674
00:38:15,920 --> 00:38:18,240
The boys naturally embodied them.

675
00:38:18,320 --> 00:38:19,680
It's great to see.

676
00:38:19,760 --> 00:38:22,200
Exhausted yet? Need a breather? Water?

677
00:38:22,280 --> 00:38:24,040
- I'm fine.
- Hey, we're good.

678
00:38:24,120 --> 00:38:27,480
I care about you guys.
Come on. This is TFM.

679
00:38:27,560 --> 00:38:29,640
- You're one band.
- We support everyone.

680
00:38:29,720 --> 00:38:30,560
TFM.

681
00:38:30,640 --> 00:38:32,960
- Take a quick break.
- Off is hilarious.

682
00:38:33,040 --> 00:38:34,760
He's so chill, as expected.

683
00:38:34,840 --> 00:38:36,720
We already knew he was laid-back.

684
00:38:36,800 --> 00:38:40,480
But teaming up as TFM? It's pure fun.

685
00:38:41,120 --> 00:38:44,000
All right, let's go.

686
00:38:45,640 --> 00:38:48,200
Why stress out?
The boys are already tense.

687
00:38:48,280 --> 00:38:50,200
I don't care what anyone else thinks.

688
00:38:50,280 --> 00:38:54,400
But my mindset from day one
is bringing everyone together.

689
00:38:54,480 --> 00:38:57,520
This boy band energy?
It's just seven guys genuinely bonding.

690
00:38:57,600 --> 00:38:59,040
I know everyone is exhausted,

691
00:38:59,120 --> 00:39:00,880
but hang in there a bit longer.

692
00:39:00,960 --> 00:39:02,240
I'm not worried.

693
00:39:02,320 --> 00:39:04,160
Because no matter what happens,

694
00:39:04,240 --> 00:39:06,120
he will improvise and make it work.

695
00:39:06,200 --> 00:39:10,920
Stick to the vision.
I want Kimhan to take the creative lead.

696
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:12,040
Okay, yes.

697
00:39:12,120 --> 00:39:13,760
- Pace yourself, dear.
- Understood.

698
00:39:13,840 --> 00:39:16,880
Dash in,
then quickly group up and interact.

699
00:39:16,960 --> 00:39:19,120
- Okay, deep breaths, everyone.
- Go interact.

700
00:39:19,200 --> 00:39:22,360
I want him to pitch ideas
and actually test them out.

701
00:39:22,440 --> 00:39:25,560
I don't want to minimize them
with rigid rules.

702
00:39:25,640 --> 00:39:28,640
I want him to execute
his own creative vision.

703
00:39:28,720 --> 00:39:30,960
Because in front of the camera,

704
00:39:31,040 --> 00:39:32,920
he knows exactly what he's capable of.

705
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:34,800
Apart from synchronized dancing,

706
00:39:34,880 --> 00:39:38,520
delivering that inner attitude
the client wants is equally crucial.

707
00:39:38,600 --> 00:39:41,160
It shows the vibe we need to convey.

708
00:39:41,240 --> 00:39:43,960
I watched the other teams
and let the ideas flow.

709
00:39:44,040 --> 00:39:45,080
Not copying, though.

710
00:39:45,160 --> 00:39:49,200
Interacting with the guys,
pulling them in during freestyle.

711
00:39:49,280 --> 00:39:51,400
We have to put ourselves in it in the end.

712
00:39:53,920 --> 00:39:55,600
Though this is a competition,

713
00:39:55,680 --> 00:39:57,440
everyone is one team.

714
00:39:57,520 --> 00:40:00,720
At the end of the day, I want everyone
to shine and look cool.

715
00:40:00,800 --> 00:40:03,800
So give it your all.
Leave it all on the floor.

716
00:40:03,880 --> 00:40:07,160
Our main focus is Kimhan.
He needs to outshine everyone.

717
00:40:07,240 --> 00:40:09,840
Don't slack. Keep the energy up.

718
00:40:13,040 --> 00:40:13,880
Let's go.

719
00:40:13,960 --> 00:40:15,320
All right!

720
00:40:16,440 --> 00:40:18,080
- Thank you.
- Fab.

721
00:40:18,160 --> 00:40:20,360
The overall vibe just clicks for me.

722
00:40:20,440 --> 00:40:23,920
It's not just a solo act
with backups in the rear.

723
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:26,720
They aren't background dancers.
We're a solid group.

724
00:40:26,800 --> 00:40:29,080
That's exactly what this campaign demands.

725
00:40:29,600 --> 00:40:32,880
It's the first time all seven of us
are working together today.

726
00:40:32,960 --> 00:40:34,640
We're one team, all right?

727
00:40:34,720 --> 00:40:36,200
- Yes.
- TFM.

728
00:40:36,800 --> 00:40:40,480
Okay, will our boys give their all
when placed on another team?

729
00:40:40,560 --> 00:40:44,160
Will the other boys give their all for us?

730
00:40:44,240 --> 00:40:48,040
Their spirit might be willing,
but after endless rehearsals…

731
00:40:48,120 --> 00:40:49,960
and having to push even harder,

732
00:40:50,560 --> 00:40:53,040
pacing themselves is crucial.

733
00:40:53,120 --> 00:40:55,560
The hook is flawless.
I saw the video, and it's great.

734
00:40:55,640 --> 00:40:57,400
Let me adjust the camera angles.

735
00:40:57,480 --> 00:41:02,160
Camera angles are everything, so I have
to brief the director of photography.

736
00:41:02,240 --> 00:41:04,440
To ensure the boys
capture the right emotion

737
00:41:04,520 --> 00:41:08,280
despite the camera setups
differing from rehearsals.

738
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:12,280
Nice, hold that. Now back up.
Break one, break two. Back up.

739
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:14,680
Cam missed the mark slightly. It's fine.

740
00:41:14,760 --> 00:41:16,320
What I need is this.

741
00:41:16,400 --> 00:41:19,640
When I say "run,"
you all sprint towards the camera.

742
00:41:19,720 --> 00:41:21,520
Should I cue the guys to fall back?

743
00:41:21,600 --> 00:41:23,360
No need. Just follow the beat.

744
00:41:24,440 --> 00:41:25,400
Run.

745
00:41:27,240 --> 00:41:30,320
Cut across the camera.
Don't run straight. Where are you going?

746
00:41:30,400 --> 00:41:32,720
Move aside.
I'll show you how it's done. Watch.

747
00:41:32,800 --> 00:41:35,920
I can't deny
I'm super intimidated by Mile.

748
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:39,040
Maybe it's just me.
I don't know about others.

749
00:41:39,120 --> 00:41:42,320
They might be fine,
but I'm low-key stressed over my team.

750
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:45,760
Back up now. The break is fast,
don't drag the beat out. Got it?

751
00:41:45,840 --> 00:41:48,920
I feel like our team
has the lowest chance of winning.

752
00:41:49,000 --> 00:41:50,960
Everyone is so stiff and just…

753
00:41:51,040 --> 00:41:53,640
Peem turns pale.
So does Bonus. Everyone too.

754
00:41:53,720 --> 00:41:55,480
The energy totally died.

755
00:41:55,560 --> 00:41:57,240
He's brutal. Absolutely savage.

756
00:41:57,320 --> 00:41:58,680
Go. Sprint in.

757
00:42:00,160 --> 00:42:01,400
Run in first, come on.

758
00:42:02,760 --> 00:42:03,800
Hold on a second.

759
00:42:03,880 --> 00:42:06,040
I need more from you all.
I know you're tired.

760
00:42:06,800 --> 00:42:09,400
Great strategy,
but a bit too intense. It's fine.

761
00:42:09,480 --> 00:42:12,480
It's his style. He may be invested
because it's his challenge.

762
00:42:12,560 --> 00:42:15,560
I'm not going to push back.
If I do, I'll get blasted.

763
00:42:15,640 --> 00:42:18,720
His blocking is insanely detailed.

764
00:42:18,800 --> 00:42:22,440
Group up, hold it, then scatter.

765
00:42:24,680 --> 00:42:27,240
The track is playing,
just follow the beat.

766
00:42:27,320 --> 00:42:31,400
I believe the rest
is entirely up to the boys.

767
00:42:31,480 --> 00:42:36,840
It's the ultimate test
of who makes it to the Final Walk.

768
00:42:42,400 --> 00:42:45,760
Welcome back to today's campaign,
"Up, Up, Clear Away."

769
00:42:45,840 --> 00:42:49,560
Today, all our contestants
will be shooting a music video

770
00:42:49,640 --> 00:42:51,520
on our custom-built set.

771
00:42:51,600 --> 00:42:54,000
Let me introduce two guest judges

772
00:42:54,080 --> 00:42:56,760
joining us to evaluate today's campaign.

773
00:42:56,840 --> 00:43:01,480
First up, a true legend in Thai showbiz.

774
00:43:01,560 --> 00:43:04,800
She has been delivering
outstanding performances for decades.

775
00:43:04,880 --> 00:43:07,840
Give it up for Nok Sinjai.

776
00:43:07,920 --> 00:43:09,600
Wow, Nok is here.

777
00:43:09,680 --> 00:43:12,200
- Hello.
- Hi, Nok.

778
00:43:12,280 --> 00:43:13,640
Hello.

779
00:43:13,720 --> 00:43:16,960
What a surprise.
I didn't expect Nok to be here.

780
00:43:17,040 --> 00:43:19,800
I just worked with her
on the series <i>Shine</i>.

781
00:43:19,880 --> 00:43:22,080
Wow, Nok is here. I'm so hyped.

782
00:43:22,720 --> 00:43:27,160
Nok, any advice
for today's music video campaign?

783
00:43:27,240 --> 00:43:29,920
Honestly, I'm as nervous
as the contestants.

784
00:43:30,000 --> 00:43:34,560
I rarely do these judging gigs.
I'm rooting for all of you.

785
00:43:34,640 --> 00:43:37,560
Just know that making it this far
is a huge achievement.

786
00:43:37,640 --> 00:43:40,680
For today, I hope everything is "Clear."

787
00:43:42,320 --> 00:43:44,560
We have one more judge.

788
00:43:44,640 --> 00:43:47,560
He's a recording artist and actor

789
00:43:47,640 --> 00:43:50,360
known for his standout style

790
00:43:50,440 --> 00:43:53,320
and viral dance moves
that took over the world.

791
00:43:53,400 --> 00:43:54,560
Timethai.

792
00:43:54,640 --> 00:43:57,320
What's up? Hello, all.

793
00:43:57,400 --> 00:43:59,160
- Hello.
- Hi.

794
00:43:59,240 --> 00:44:02,880
It feels like I'm looking back
at my younger self.

795
00:44:02,960 --> 00:44:05,880
Timethai. He's a singer
with the smoothest moves.

796
00:44:05,960 --> 00:44:07,240
Our three mentors.

797
00:44:07,320 --> 00:44:09,720
Do you have anything to say to our judges?

798
00:44:09,800 --> 00:44:11,760
Please be generous with scores.

799
00:44:11,840 --> 00:44:14,680
I only have one guy left
because someone here is ruthless.

800
00:44:14,760 --> 00:44:16,800
- But he's giving it his all.
- So shameless.

801
00:44:16,880 --> 00:44:20,000
- Who's she talking about?
- He's putting up a real fight.

802
00:44:20,080 --> 00:44:21,480
- His name is Kimhan.
- Got it.

803
00:44:21,560 --> 00:44:23,040
- Okay.
- Look out for him.

804
00:44:24,480 --> 00:44:29,000
My bad, guys.
I didn't mean for this to happen.

805
00:44:30,880 --> 00:44:33,800
All right, our first team
is ready to roll.

806
00:44:33,880 --> 00:44:36,000
Let's welcome Team Off.

807
00:44:37,560 --> 00:44:41,200
- Hello.
- Hello.

808
00:44:41,280 --> 00:44:45,280
The first set involves
jumping from a floating house

809
00:44:45,360 --> 00:44:46,400
with a Clear balloon.

810
00:44:46,480 --> 00:44:49,000
Each team gets exactly five minutes.

811
00:44:49,080 --> 00:44:50,760
- Bonus, you're up first.
- Got it.

812
00:44:50,840 --> 00:44:53,960
Let Bonus set the bar.
I want to see his energy.

813
00:44:54,040 --> 00:44:56,200
I saw the stairs and the crash mat.

814
00:44:56,280 --> 00:44:57,720
Oh, crap, I have to jump?

815
00:44:57,800 --> 00:44:59,280
Start the clock.

816
00:44:59,360 --> 00:45:03,480
Take two or three steps, then jump.
Leaping into it looks better.

817
00:45:03,560 --> 00:45:06,040
Otherwise, it's like
you're falling off a building.

818
00:45:06,120 --> 00:45:07,600
Man, I'll do whatever it takes.

819
00:45:07,680 --> 00:45:11,160
I already kissed Do on the lips.
A little jump is nothing.

820
00:45:13,320 --> 00:45:16,480
- Hold up.
- Oh, shit. Sorry, man.

821
00:45:16,560 --> 00:45:18,480
Let's run it again. Go.

822
00:45:18,560 --> 00:45:20,440
I almost stepped right on his head.

823
00:45:20,520 --> 00:45:23,200
Look confident. Go clear things up.
Go get the girl.

824
00:45:25,000 --> 00:45:25,880
Ready? Action.

825
00:45:29,120 --> 00:45:32,240
Nice. Looks great.
Can we play back the footage?

826
00:45:32,320 --> 00:45:33,600
One minute down.

827
00:45:33,680 --> 00:45:35,600
Pause the clock. Let's check playback.

828
00:45:35,680 --> 00:45:37,520
We can't. This is the process.

829
00:45:37,600 --> 00:45:38,800
- No.
- Clock doesn't stop.

830
00:45:38,880 --> 00:45:41,400
Can I see the playback? Please? Playback?

831
00:45:42,320 --> 00:45:43,360
Pause the clock, guys.

832
00:45:43,440 --> 00:45:44,760
- Pause the timer.
- Let's see.

833
00:45:45,600 --> 00:45:47,080
Chill out, Off.

834
00:45:47,160 --> 00:45:50,680
Off is definitely way more stressed
than usual today.

835
00:45:50,760 --> 00:45:51,960
So stressed.

836
00:45:52,040 --> 00:45:53,800
I'm up first. You get to copy me.

837
00:45:53,880 --> 00:45:56,520
- You get to play back.
- You know how it feels to go first?

838
00:45:56,600 --> 00:45:58,560
Skip the playback. Let's move on.

839
00:45:58,640 --> 00:46:01,160
Is it just me,
or is he terrified of losing?

840
00:46:01,240 --> 00:46:04,200
Make it up with your girl shyly.
Be yourself, though.

841
00:46:04,280 --> 00:46:05,960
Give us that cute kitten vibe.

842
00:46:08,760 --> 00:46:10,240
Yes, that's good.

843
00:46:10,320 --> 00:46:13,880
Now we have to see how the slow-mo
and his facial expressions turn out.

844
00:46:13,960 --> 00:46:17,160
The height doesn't faze me at all.
I just jumped and bam.

845
00:46:18,120 --> 00:46:19,720
Another take, Pom.

846
00:46:19,800 --> 00:46:21,160
I hurt my back.

847
00:46:21,240 --> 00:46:22,720
Ready? Okay.

848
00:46:24,560 --> 00:46:26,920
Yes. Great pose. That's it.

849
00:46:27,000 --> 00:46:29,400
I always trust that Pom will deliver.

850
00:46:29,480 --> 00:46:30,840
- Okay. We're good.
- Okay.

851
00:46:30,920 --> 00:46:32,480
They'll say I'm cheating.

852
00:46:32,560 --> 00:46:34,720
This is the one episode
you're not cheating.

853
00:46:36,600 --> 00:46:38,840
Mile, don't say a word.
Keep your mouth shut.

854
00:46:38,920 --> 00:46:40,880
Next up, Team Mentor Mile.

855
00:46:42,240 --> 00:46:44,160
Hold on. Give Nok a proper greeting.

856
00:46:44,240 --> 00:46:47,000
- Hello.
- Hello.

857
00:46:47,080 --> 00:46:49,080
Give Timethai a killer dance move.

858
00:46:52,880 --> 00:46:53,760
Timethai.

859
00:46:53,840 --> 00:46:55,160
He's my idol.

860
00:46:55,240 --> 00:46:58,680
Can we get some background music?
To help them get into the groove.

861
00:46:58,760 --> 00:46:59,600
Clock is ticking.

862
00:46:59,680 --> 00:47:00,960
Gluf, you're up first.

863
00:47:01,040 --> 00:47:04,080
Anything is fine,
but your right hand holds the ice cream.

864
00:47:04,160 --> 00:47:05,160
Hand holding it…

865
00:47:05,240 --> 00:47:09,960
The MV needs to flow with the song.
Match the dynamics and feel the vibe.

866
00:47:10,040 --> 00:47:11,200
When you're ready.

867
00:47:11,280 --> 00:47:12,680
Holding the ice cream means…

868
00:47:12,760 --> 00:47:14,240
Even if you're eating it.

869
00:47:14,320 --> 00:47:19,680
The client wants the balloons
to look like they're lifting us up.

870
00:47:19,760 --> 00:47:22,200
You're leaving the house
to meet your girl. Go.

871
00:47:22,280 --> 00:47:23,880
Three, two, one, action!

872
00:47:25,000 --> 00:47:25,920
Go!

873
00:47:26,000 --> 00:47:26,840
That's cute.

874
00:47:26,920 --> 00:47:29,960
When Gluf jumps, it's like
he's going to see his girlfriend.

875
00:47:34,400 --> 00:47:36,680
- The last one is adorable.
- That works, right?

876
00:47:36,760 --> 00:47:39,560
Do you really have the balls?
We'll see it right here.

877
00:47:43,000 --> 00:47:44,720
I didn't expect to fall that fast.

878
00:47:44,800 --> 00:47:47,200
I fell before I could even tuck
my legs in.

879
00:47:47,280 --> 00:47:49,040
Landed flat on my feet.

880
00:47:50,760 --> 00:47:52,000
Peem, your turn. Let's go.

881
00:47:52,080 --> 00:47:54,680
Ready? Take it easy. Relax.

882
00:47:55,200 --> 00:47:56,240
Yes!

883
00:47:57,120 --> 00:47:58,240
First round was okay.

884
00:47:58,320 --> 00:48:00,360
The second round wasn't bad either.

885
00:48:01,360 --> 00:48:02,200
Got it!

886
00:48:02,280 --> 00:48:04,800
- I'm going, I'm going.
- Okay.

887
00:48:04,880 --> 00:48:06,360
Can the mentor get points too?

888
00:48:07,000 --> 00:48:08,880
Dance, dance. Ready? Go.

889
00:48:12,760 --> 00:48:16,440
By the third round, it's starting to hurt.
Will the audience think I am floating?

890
00:48:16,520 --> 00:48:18,000
That is up to the editors now.

891
00:48:21,720 --> 00:48:23,000
Time's up!

892
00:48:23,080 --> 00:48:24,240
- Okay.
- Nice.

893
00:48:24,320 --> 00:48:26,680
Next up, Team Pancake-Ananda.

894
00:48:26,760 --> 00:48:28,920
Start the clock. You have five minutes.

895
00:48:29,000 --> 00:48:31,360
So nervous. I've been tense all day.

896
00:48:31,440 --> 00:48:32,720
I rehearsed a lot.

897
00:48:32,800 --> 00:48:34,280
Hope I don't mess up.

898
00:48:36,040 --> 00:48:37,240
Terrified today.

899
00:48:37,320 --> 00:48:39,040
- He's scared of heights.
- Really?

900
00:48:39,120 --> 00:48:40,080
Look at his eyes.

901
00:48:41,200 --> 00:48:42,160
Terrified of heights.

902
00:48:43,320 --> 00:48:46,360
Give me your biggest smile.
Look super happy. Step forward.

903
00:48:46,960 --> 00:48:50,280
Someone wants you to clear everything out.
Be confident, be happy.

904
00:48:51,360 --> 00:48:52,640
Give me another cool one.

905
00:48:53,240 --> 00:48:55,800
His face looks so tense.
Maybe he feels pressure.

906
00:48:55,880 --> 00:48:56,880
He's so serious.

907
00:48:59,280 --> 00:49:00,600
Okay.

908
00:49:00,680 --> 00:49:03,240
- Do you need anything else?
- Mentor, care to jump?

909
00:49:03,320 --> 00:49:04,640
- Hey!
- Hey!

910
00:49:04,720 --> 00:49:05,720
Don't do that.

911
00:49:05,800 --> 00:49:07,920
- Just asking.
- Asked the client. Five minutes.

912
00:49:08,000 --> 00:49:10,040
Kim, give us two more. Vary it.

913
00:49:10,120 --> 00:49:11,480
He's got time to nail it.

914
00:49:11,560 --> 00:49:14,040
So there's no need to rush.

915
00:49:14,120 --> 00:49:15,400
Your biggest smile.

916
00:49:16,080 --> 00:49:17,600
- That's it.
- That's it.

917
00:49:17,680 --> 00:49:19,160
Keep yourself in check.

918
00:49:19,240 --> 00:49:20,840
Forty-five seconds left.

919
00:49:20,920 --> 00:49:22,560
I'm going there to clear it up.

920
00:49:22,640 --> 00:49:24,320
- There we go.
- That's it.

921
00:49:25,440 --> 00:49:26,920
I probably jumped over ten times.

922
00:49:27,000 --> 00:49:29,600
The judges said I looked stressed.
I was exhausted.

923
00:49:29,680 --> 00:49:30,640
Just me jumping.

924
00:49:30,720 --> 00:49:32,480
Nobody to vibe with, doing it solo.

925
00:49:32,560 --> 00:49:33,880
Yes, no buddies around.

926
00:49:37,480 --> 00:49:39,240
Enough, you're done. Stop.

927
00:49:39,320 --> 00:49:41,400
- Thanks, Team Pancake-Ananda.
- Thanks.

928
00:49:41,480 --> 00:49:44,400
Team Pancake is a one-man show.
Kimhan jumped for his life.

929
00:49:44,480 --> 00:49:46,880
Like, damn, bring it on.

930
00:49:46,960 --> 00:49:50,920
I know our team has plenty of good shots.
A lot of great, varied options.

931
00:49:51,000 --> 00:49:53,200
If I were Pancake,
I would've jumped for him.

932
00:49:53,280 --> 00:49:54,400
Oh, really now?

933
00:49:54,920 --> 00:49:56,960
- Mile, you're getting cocky.
- Way too cocky.

934
00:49:57,040 --> 00:49:58,920
You're all over the place today.

935
00:49:59,000 --> 00:49:59,880
Just a little bit.

936
00:49:59,960 --> 00:50:02,920
Next up, we're shooting the chorus scene.

937
00:50:03,000 --> 00:50:06,120
Each team will have
exactly 15 minutes to shoot.

938
00:50:06,720 --> 00:50:10,080
Let's welcome the first team.
Team Off with the ice scene.

939
00:50:10,160 --> 00:50:12,320
Can we get some TFM energy?

940
00:50:12,400 --> 00:50:13,440
Our squad.

941
00:50:13,520 --> 00:50:14,760
Five, four, three, two…

942
00:50:14,840 --> 00:50:15,840
- TFM!
- TFM!

943
00:50:17,560 --> 00:50:20,080
Next is the chorus choreography.

944
00:50:20,160 --> 00:50:21,920
I'm still panting from jumping.

945
00:50:22,000 --> 00:50:23,240
Now I have to dance.

946
00:50:23,320 --> 00:50:24,720
Let's go. Music.

947
00:50:29,680 --> 00:50:30,800
Let's go.

948
00:50:30,880 --> 00:50:32,720
- They're good.
- They're killing it.

949
00:50:34,080 --> 00:50:36,680
I was nervous at first
since we're the first team up.

950
00:50:36,760 --> 00:50:38,320
I'm afraid of messing up.

951
00:50:40,000 --> 00:50:41,280
Camera pushing in.

952
00:50:43,720 --> 00:50:46,560
Not like that. Push in like I told you.

953
00:50:46,640 --> 00:50:49,200
Track it first. Again. We got this.

954
00:50:49,280 --> 00:50:51,840
At first, the cameraman
kept coming in wrong.

955
00:50:51,920 --> 00:50:55,160
He already apologized.
I'm not holding a grudge.

956
00:50:55,240 --> 00:50:56,960
I'll see it as a rehearsal round.

957
00:50:57,040 --> 00:50:59,040
Okay, music.

958
00:51:01,520 --> 00:51:03,560
Love that.

959
00:51:03,640 --> 00:51:05,360
So good. Yes, perfect.

960
00:51:06,160 --> 00:51:08,600
- Work those hips.
- Work them.

961
00:51:11,880 --> 00:51:13,320
Why are you laughing so loud?

962
00:51:14,440 --> 00:51:15,320
I felt the vibe.

963
00:51:15,400 --> 00:51:19,520
Bonus gave us those signature hips today,
but turned them up even more.

964
00:51:19,600 --> 00:51:21,840
He was serving pure sweetness out there.

965
00:51:22,680 --> 00:51:24,280
Just frame the middle three.

966
00:51:24,360 --> 00:51:26,400
Who said they can't dance? They're great.

967
00:51:26,480 --> 00:51:27,880
Yes, they're great dancers.

968
00:51:27,960 --> 00:51:29,920
Bonus looks so relaxed.

969
00:51:30,000 --> 00:51:33,080
I don't know, he didn't seem stressed
about the choreo at all.

970
00:51:33,160 --> 00:51:36,640
Watching him genuinely made it
fun for us too.

971
00:51:36,720 --> 00:51:38,480
Pom, you're the center.

972
00:51:39,160 --> 00:51:40,960
Catch your breath. Take it easy.

973
00:51:41,040 --> 00:51:42,280
Take a break.

974
00:51:42,360 --> 00:51:43,400
I'd be exhausted too.

975
00:51:43,480 --> 00:51:46,680
Looking tired on camera is a bad look.

976
00:51:46,760 --> 00:51:48,120
Relax, no rush.

977
00:51:48,200 --> 00:51:49,440
Music.

978
00:51:57,840 --> 00:52:00,600
- He has that cheeky vibe.
- He never breaks eye contact.

979
00:52:02,520 --> 00:52:04,920
He's giving Por Unnop energy.

980
00:52:05,000 --> 00:52:06,640
I'm really proud of myself.

981
00:52:06,720 --> 00:52:08,680
I have zero dance background.

982
00:52:08,760 --> 00:52:12,040
I feel like I did it well.
Honestly, it was iconic. I nailed it.

983
00:52:12,120 --> 00:52:15,280
Look at Pom,
the second he smiles and dances,

984
00:52:15,360 --> 00:52:17,200
he totally owns the camera.

985
00:52:17,280 --> 00:52:19,760
Rome, for your end pose,
give me a tiger, whatever.

986
00:52:19,840 --> 00:52:21,880
- Got it.
- Push it until you drop.

987
00:52:21,960 --> 00:52:24,080
Honestly, that's great. We can wrap it up.

988
00:52:24,160 --> 00:52:25,280
Breathe.

989
00:52:25,360 --> 00:52:26,320
Is this Off's plan?

990
00:52:26,400 --> 00:52:28,160
To totally drain our energy?

991
00:52:28,240 --> 00:52:30,360
Forty seconds left.

992
00:52:32,920 --> 00:52:35,120
Go, Rome. Serve the fangirls.

993
00:52:35,200 --> 00:52:36,600
Give them what they want.

994
00:52:38,000 --> 00:52:39,240
Look at this.

995
00:52:40,200 --> 00:52:42,240
Oh, you crazy kid!

996
00:52:47,160 --> 00:52:49,400
They're all panting heavily.

997
00:52:49,480 --> 00:52:51,720
Panting, but keeping in character.

998
00:52:52,560 --> 00:52:53,800
The ending fairy.

999
00:52:53,880 --> 00:52:55,680
The cute, innocent panting.

1000
00:52:55,760 --> 00:52:57,800
The sweaty athlete panting.

1001
00:52:57,880 --> 00:52:59,120
The cool, flirty panting.

1002
00:52:59,200 --> 00:53:00,680
Pure K-Pop visuals.

1003
00:53:00,760 --> 00:53:02,360
The shy panting.

1004
00:53:04,560 --> 00:53:06,880
Tiger kiss!

1005
00:53:06,960 --> 00:53:08,840
Oh, you are so dead tonight.

1006
00:53:10,520 --> 00:53:11,960
Yes, flawless.

1007
00:53:13,560 --> 00:53:14,440
Okay.

1008
00:53:14,520 --> 00:53:17,400
- Thank you, everyone.
- Thank you!

1009
00:53:17,480 --> 00:53:20,000
The brand doesn't want to see
you exhausted.

1010
00:53:20,080 --> 00:53:22,240
Looking tired gives us unusable footage.

1011
00:53:23,040 --> 00:53:25,720
Next up, Mentor Mile and the meadow scene.

1012
00:53:25,800 --> 00:53:27,360
Wait before you start the clock.

1013
00:53:27,440 --> 00:53:28,520
No, start it now.

1014
00:53:28,600 --> 00:53:30,680
- I haven't gone up yet.
- It's nothing.

1015
00:53:30,760 --> 00:53:33,880
I've got some red envelopes
for my four boys in the back.

1016
00:53:33,960 --> 00:53:36,520
- Fifteen minutes, go!
- Here, split this.

1017
00:53:36,600 --> 00:53:38,240
Are you bribing them?

1018
00:53:38,320 --> 00:53:39,880
Spoiling his team.

1019
00:53:39,960 --> 00:53:43,360
Wow, bringing props to bribe the boys?That

1020
00:53:43,440 --> 00:53:44,960
He solves problems with money.

1021
00:53:45,040 --> 00:53:46,080
Is this a bribe?

1022
00:53:46,160 --> 00:53:47,160
Absolutely.

1023
00:53:47,240 --> 00:53:50,960
You call me a cheater, but bribing
with cash isn't cheating? That's a bribe.

1024
00:53:51,040 --> 00:53:52,480
If they win, it'll be sketchy.

1025
00:53:52,560 --> 00:53:56,120
It's an incentive. To clear their minds
and perform their best.

1026
00:53:56,200 --> 00:53:58,800
Off, if you need to clear your mind,
use the shampoo.

1027
00:53:58,880 --> 00:53:59,960
You'll feel clear.

1028
00:54:00,040 --> 00:54:01,240
Cheater.

1029
00:54:01,320 --> 00:54:03,600
Peem, stay in the center. Got it?

1030
00:54:03,680 --> 00:54:05,080
Music.

1031
00:54:05,160 --> 00:54:07,080
Twist slowly, Peem. Twist.

1032
00:54:07,880 --> 00:54:10,880
To the left, right. Lean into the center.

1033
00:54:10,960 --> 00:54:11,920
Lean to the center.

1034
00:54:12,000 --> 00:54:14,280
Come into the center. Stop.

1035
00:54:14,360 --> 00:54:15,920
Stop!

1036
00:54:16,000 --> 00:54:17,000
Tag in.

1037
00:54:18,120 --> 00:54:19,120
Step in a bit more.

1038
00:54:19,800 --> 00:54:20,960
Add a little twist.

1039
00:54:21,040 --> 00:54:22,160
Since the first campaign,

1040
00:54:22,240 --> 00:54:24,640
it's the first time
Mile looks this serious.

1041
00:54:24,720 --> 00:54:26,520
He's actually taking it seriously.

1042
00:54:26,600 --> 00:54:28,240
Look at his methods.

1043
00:54:28,320 --> 00:54:29,480
Directing every angle.

1044
00:54:29,560 --> 00:54:34,760
Just a few takes of dancing,
and I'm totally drenched in sweat.

1045
00:54:34,840 --> 00:54:38,400
Mile looked super stressed and intense,
so I went to mess with him.

1046
00:54:38,480 --> 00:54:40,880
Go, excellent. Give it your all.

1047
00:54:43,440 --> 00:54:44,720
But he totally ignored me.

1048
00:54:44,800 --> 00:54:47,080
When I'm coaching, I'm fully in the zone.

1049
00:54:47,160 --> 00:54:49,320
I want the final product to be flawless.

1050
00:54:49,400 --> 00:54:53,800
It's good. Finally taking it seriously.
Just in time for the final campaign.

1051
00:54:53,880 --> 00:54:55,120
Gluf, stay in the middle.

1052
00:54:55,200 --> 00:54:57,080
Keep the character Off gave you.

1053
00:54:57,160 --> 00:54:59,400
Off is sweet.
He even planned it out for me.

1054
00:54:59,480 --> 00:55:02,240
- I did not!
- Guide characters for the kids?

1055
00:55:02,320 --> 00:55:04,920
You can't just have me do your job, Mile.

1056
00:55:11,880 --> 00:55:13,400
Wow, he's so cute.

1057
00:55:16,800 --> 00:55:18,560
Honestly, this guy's got moves.

1058
00:55:18,640 --> 00:55:20,120
Gluf is 16, the youngest.

1059
00:55:20,200 --> 00:55:21,600
He has great musicality.

1060
00:55:21,680 --> 00:55:24,640
He listens to the music
and stays aware of his surroundings.

1061
00:55:24,720 --> 00:55:26,960
I find him really interesting.

1062
00:55:27,040 --> 00:55:28,680
The last minute!

1063
00:55:29,920 --> 00:55:31,480
Deep breaths.

1064
00:55:32,640 --> 00:55:33,800
Breathe deep.

1065
00:55:33,880 --> 00:55:35,080
Breathe deep, Mile.

1066
00:55:35,160 --> 00:55:37,320
- Get Mile some water.
- I'm good, really.

1067
00:55:37,400 --> 00:55:40,160
- Take it easy.
- I'm still young, thanks.

1068
00:55:42,040 --> 00:55:43,880
First time hearing Mile speak today.

1069
00:55:44,480 --> 00:55:46,640
I let him play with Off this whole time.

1070
00:55:48,520 --> 00:55:49,720
Step in!

1071
00:55:51,520 --> 00:55:53,840
Step back. Stop.

1072
00:55:54,440 --> 00:55:56,080
I think it's okay. We got this.

1073
00:55:56,160 --> 00:55:59,360
Run like your life depends on it.
Three, two, one, go.

1074
00:55:59,440 --> 00:56:00,440
Give it everything.

1075
00:56:00,520 --> 00:56:02,320
Last 30 seconds.

1076
00:56:03,680 --> 00:56:05,560
Where exactly are they running to?

1077
00:56:05,640 --> 00:56:06,840
Running home?

1078
00:56:07,600 --> 00:56:10,200
Now, for our final team
shooting the chorus.

1079
00:56:10,280 --> 00:56:12,320
Team Pancake-Ananda.

1080
00:56:12,400 --> 00:56:13,560
It's our time to shine.

1081
00:56:13,640 --> 00:56:16,000
Panda. The one and only.

1082
00:56:16,080 --> 00:56:18,480
- Come on.
- I totally get him now.

1083
00:56:18,560 --> 00:56:20,240
Seeing you dance so much,
I understand you.

1084
00:56:20,320 --> 00:56:21,920
- Don't stress.
- Got it.

1085
00:56:22,000 --> 00:56:23,400
Fifteen minutes, start!

1086
00:56:23,480 --> 00:56:25,080
One soft run-through.

1087
00:56:28,080 --> 00:56:29,600
When it's Pancake's turn…

1088
00:56:29,680 --> 00:56:32,080
Is this a whole team,
or just a one-man show?

1089
00:56:34,000 --> 00:56:36,480
We only have one guy, but he delivers.

1090
00:56:36,560 --> 00:56:39,240
You have too many guys.
It's a waste of time.

1091
00:56:41,360 --> 00:56:43,120
He's always frowning like this.

1092
00:56:43,200 --> 00:56:44,600
You need to loosen up.

1093
00:56:48,600 --> 00:56:49,840
First take was beautiful.

1094
00:56:49,920 --> 00:56:52,760
But at the end,
slipped and tripped over Gluf's foot.

1095
00:56:52,840 --> 00:56:55,000
Great, I ruined my friend's take.

1096
00:56:55,080 --> 00:56:58,120
As for Kimhan, no matter how good
his performance is,

1097
00:56:58,200 --> 00:57:00,440
his facial expressions just fell flat.

1098
00:57:02,640 --> 00:57:04,280
- He's more relaxed.
- It's better.

1099
00:57:04,880 --> 00:57:05,880
Much better.

1100
00:57:05,960 --> 00:57:09,560
Come on, let me hear the crowd!

1101
00:57:11,480 --> 00:57:12,880
The second round was better.

1102
00:57:13,960 --> 00:57:16,240
- It could be better.
- Five minutes left.

1103
00:57:16,320 --> 00:57:18,080
Let's make this the final take.

1104
00:57:20,480 --> 00:57:21,680
I want to scream too.

1105
00:57:21,760 --> 00:57:22,720
Scream.

1106
00:57:23,960 --> 00:57:26,040
What's wrong with my voice?

1107
00:57:26,120 --> 00:57:27,960
I'm wondering too. What's with my voice?

1108
00:57:28,840 --> 00:57:31,680
I changed his blocking a bit
during the actual shoot.

1109
00:57:31,760 --> 00:57:33,520
It wasn't something we rehearsed.

1110
00:57:33,600 --> 00:57:37,000
Running out of frame, rushing back in
to kind of greet his friends.

1111
00:57:42,000 --> 00:57:44,240
Just one guy left.
First, he's easy to coach.

1112
00:57:44,320 --> 00:57:47,120
Second, he gets endless takes.

1113
00:57:47,200 --> 00:57:49,000
It's a massive advantage.

1114
00:57:52,720 --> 00:57:54,280
Okay.

1115
00:57:54,360 --> 00:57:57,120
It was cute. No one was left behind.

1116
00:57:57,200 --> 00:57:59,640
They gave it their all,
even when it wasn't their parts.

1117
00:57:59,720 --> 00:58:02,960
All right, we've finally reached
the freestyle section.

1118
00:58:03,040 --> 00:58:06,440
Each team only gets five minutes.

1119
00:58:06,520 --> 00:58:07,880
Team Off, you're up.

1120
00:58:07,960 --> 00:58:09,960
TFM, you remember your cues, right?

1121
00:58:10,040 --> 00:58:11,600
- Yes.
- Everyone got their marks?

1122
00:58:11,680 --> 00:58:13,200
For freestyle, it's all seven.

1123
00:58:13,280 --> 00:58:17,160
We form a semi-circle
and step out to dance one by one.

1124
00:58:17,840 --> 00:58:19,080
Come on.

1125
00:58:19,720 --> 00:58:21,200
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

1126
00:58:29,400 --> 00:58:31,760
We are exhausted, but our spirits are not.

1127
00:58:31,840 --> 00:58:34,640
Dance. Cha-cha.

1128
00:58:35,720 --> 00:58:37,320
Rome is losing it.

1129
00:58:37,400 --> 00:58:38,960
So cute.

1130
00:58:43,280 --> 00:58:45,000
He's corrupting my boy!

1131
00:58:46,200 --> 00:58:47,680
I went dancing with Bonus.

1132
00:58:47,760 --> 00:58:48,800
We had to go all out.

1133
00:58:48,880 --> 00:58:51,560
Zero focus, zero sanity.
The music is all I need.

1134
00:58:51,640 --> 00:58:52,560
Just let it flow.

1135
00:58:58,680 --> 00:59:00,840
Rome steps in, boom.

1136
00:59:00,920 --> 00:59:02,360
Turn the cam for a group shot.

1137
00:59:03,600 --> 00:59:04,600
Perfect ending.

1138
00:59:04,680 --> 00:59:07,040
Next up, Team Mentor Mile.

1139
00:59:07,120 --> 00:59:10,280
Don't forget the intro, guys. Duck down.

1140
00:59:10,360 --> 00:59:11,200
Start the clock.

1141
00:59:11,280 --> 00:59:13,120
Look into the lens. Pierce it.

1142
00:59:13,200 --> 00:59:16,840
His honorary team member, the cameraman.
Directed him more than his boys.

1143
00:59:16,920 --> 00:59:19,680
Three, two, one, hit the camera.

1144
00:59:20,640 --> 00:59:22,800
The whole gang is tagging in.

1145
00:59:22,880 --> 00:59:26,280
Get in there. Have fun.

1146
00:59:26,360 --> 00:59:27,800
Gluf, you're up. Solo.

1147
00:59:29,320 --> 00:59:31,480
It's the final round. Screw it all.

1148
00:59:31,560 --> 00:59:34,080
Just hoping it turns out great.

1149
00:59:34,160 --> 00:59:36,400
Get a little closer to the camera.

1150
00:59:36,480 --> 00:59:38,080
Clear, clear, clear.

1151
00:59:38,160 --> 00:59:40,560
Gluf knows how to work a smile.

1152
00:59:40,640 --> 00:59:43,320
He can lock it in and still look natural.

1153
00:59:43,400 --> 00:59:45,680
Manyoo, 54, 49, or 56. Right here.

1154
00:59:45,760 --> 00:59:48,840
What's Manyoo's score?

1155
00:59:48,920 --> 00:59:50,160
What even is this?

1156
00:59:50,240 --> 00:59:52,160
Can I pass this question? It's 60.

1157
00:59:55,640 --> 00:59:57,440
Let me hear some noise in the studio.

1158
01:00:01,360 --> 01:00:04,000
At that moment,
I knew it was the final round.

1159
01:00:04,080 --> 01:00:07,360
I gave it my all.
I didn't save energy for anything else.

1160
01:00:07,440 --> 01:00:10,760
I was just completely exhausted.
But nobody was backing down.

1161
01:00:11,680 --> 01:00:14,200
- Make It Clear. Let's go.
- Make It Clear.

1162
01:00:14,280 --> 01:00:16,080
- Time's up.
- Got it.

1163
01:00:16,160 --> 01:00:17,480
Thank you.

1164
01:00:18,560 --> 01:00:20,360
I only had to sweat through it once.

1165
01:00:20,440 --> 01:00:23,320
He had to do it twice,
running and swiping the camera.

1166
01:00:23,400 --> 01:00:25,120
It probably won't get used.

1167
01:00:25,720 --> 01:00:28,360
Now we're down to the final team.

1168
01:00:28,440 --> 01:00:29,800
Team Pancake-Ananda.

1169
01:00:30,440 --> 01:00:31,760
Towel, please.

1170
01:00:32,320 --> 01:00:35,920
I never imagined being on <i>The Face Men</i>
would feel quite like this.

1171
01:00:36,000 --> 01:00:39,160
Beyond the fierce competition,
it's the spirit of these guys.

1172
01:00:39,240 --> 01:00:42,400
It's the genuine sincerity
and brotherhood they share.

1173
01:00:43,000 --> 01:00:45,680
Our team's concept
is being stranded in a desert.

1174
01:00:45,760 --> 01:00:47,320
Scorching and sweltering.

1175
01:00:47,400 --> 01:00:50,680
But we instantly feel refreshed
once we use Clear.

1176
01:00:50,760 --> 01:00:51,920
The clock is ticking.

1177
01:00:54,360 --> 01:00:58,080
This is your last chance to dance.
Give it all out on the floor.

1178
01:01:01,200 --> 01:01:02,520
Just let loose.

1179
01:01:06,920 --> 01:01:08,120
Let loose.

1180
01:01:08,200 --> 01:01:10,040
Do whatever you want. Feel the vibe.

1181
01:01:10,120 --> 01:01:14,320
It's the end of the campaign.
Go all out. Stick to the plan.

1182
01:01:14,400 --> 01:01:16,240
- Who's next?
- Bonus, let's go.

1183
01:01:19,640 --> 01:01:21,560
Work those hips.

1184
01:01:22,320 --> 01:01:24,280
Serve it.

1185
01:01:28,840 --> 01:01:32,480
Looking at today's drafts,
every team really had each other's backs.

1186
01:01:32,560 --> 01:01:33,800
It's amazing to see.

1187
01:01:33,880 --> 01:01:35,160
Thirty seconds left.

1188
01:01:36,520 --> 01:01:40,120
Dancing, shooting a music video,
it drains so much of your energy.

1189
01:01:40,200 --> 01:01:44,440
The boys get to learn what it takes
to make it in this industry.

1190
01:01:44,520 --> 01:01:46,600
You have to go through quite a tough time.

1191
01:01:46,680 --> 01:01:49,760
I'm impressed to see
their relentless energy today.

1192
01:01:49,840 --> 01:01:51,440
Give it your all.

1193
01:01:52,200 --> 01:01:53,160
Come on.

1194
01:01:58,560 --> 01:02:01,680
This was another brutally tough
campaign for the boys.

1195
01:02:01,760 --> 01:02:03,840
Especially for Kimhan, being totally solo.

1196
01:02:03,920 --> 01:02:06,920
If he weren't such a well-liked guy,

1197
01:02:07,000 --> 01:02:09,640
this magic would not
have come together so effortlessly.

1198
01:02:09,720 --> 01:02:11,640
When it was all over,

1199
01:02:11,720 --> 01:02:15,280
it hit me that we'll never get to do
something like this together again.

1200
01:02:15,360 --> 01:02:17,960
It's bittersweet.
I'm sad but also so happy.

1201
01:02:20,240 --> 01:02:23,600
My heart is so full. We're a family.

1202
01:02:23,680 --> 01:02:26,880
I never thought I would make it
to Episode 7.

1203
01:02:27,840 --> 01:02:30,400
Wrapping it up
and seeing everyone's faces…

1204
01:02:31,320 --> 01:02:32,440
They killed it.

1205
01:02:33,000 --> 01:02:38,560
I want to prove that ordinary people
can achieve the unimaginable.

1206
01:02:38,640 --> 01:02:40,200
If you commit, you can do it.

1207
01:02:42,480 --> 01:02:45,000
I want to be everyone's inspiration.

1208
01:02:51,520 --> 01:02:54,960
All right. Before we reveal the results
of today's competition,

1209
01:02:55,040 --> 01:02:58,240
let's hear some feedback from our judges.

1210
01:02:58,320 --> 01:03:00,160
- Golf, what are your thoughts?
- Right.

1211
01:03:00,240 --> 01:03:03,440
First, I have to say I'm incredibly
impressed by all seven guys.

1212
01:03:03,520 --> 01:03:07,280
We watched them grow from the very
first campaigns and master classes.

1213
01:03:07,360 --> 01:03:11,680
Their evolution is on another level.
They did an amazing job.

1214
01:03:11,760 --> 01:03:16,000
What I loved the most was the vibe.
It didn't feel like a competition.

1215
01:03:16,080 --> 01:03:18,320
They were doing everything to work as one.

1216
01:03:18,400 --> 01:03:19,520
Supporting each other.

1217
01:03:19,600 --> 01:03:23,160
I completely agree.
It's beyond a competition now.

1218
01:03:23,240 --> 01:03:25,400
They are so united as a team.

1219
01:03:25,480 --> 01:03:28,560
They worked to make magic happen
and pull off a flawless shoot.

1220
01:03:28,640 --> 01:03:33,480
I really have to applaud the boys
and the mentors too.

1221
01:03:33,560 --> 01:03:35,040
- They're well-trained.
- Thanks.

1222
01:03:35,120 --> 01:03:40,080
Their growth is insane.
Honestly, they're all looking like stars.

1223
01:03:40,680 --> 01:03:44,800
I just hope they keep this fierce energy
right up to the finale.

1224
01:03:44,880 --> 01:03:45,880
- Thank you.
- Now…

1225
01:03:45,960 --> 01:03:47,400
Let's break it down by team.

1226
01:03:47,480 --> 01:03:49,520
- Sounds good.
- Let's start with Team Off.

1227
01:03:49,600 --> 01:03:51,160
- Golf, your thoughts?
- Sure.

1228
01:03:51,240 --> 01:03:54,880
For the first team, the best part
was their individual characters.

1229
01:03:54,960 --> 01:03:57,200
They were clear and incredibly natural.

1230
01:03:57,280 --> 01:03:59,680
It was a joy to watch.
They just flowed together.

1231
01:03:59,760 --> 01:04:01,960
Everyone brought
their authentic selves to the camera.

1232
01:04:02,040 --> 01:04:03,360
- Right.
- For example…

1233
01:04:03,440 --> 01:04:06,360
The guys who aren't usually
as comfortable in their own skin

1234
01:04:06,440 --> 01:04:10,040
really focused on working the camera
and finding their rhythm.

1235
01:04:10,120 --> 01:04:13,200
- Totally speechless. Just let them play.
- Exactly.

1236
01:04:13,280 --> 01:04:15,400
And they executed it perfectly.

1237
01:04:15,480 --> 01:04:18,240
The overall vibe of this team
was just a perfect blend.

1238
01:04:18,320 --> 01:04:20,880
It arguably outshone
the other teams today.

1239
01:04:20,960 --> 01:04:23,760
Given the boys' personalities…
And I'd say Bonus

1240
01:04:23,840 --> 01:04:26,360
was definitely one
of the biggest standouts today.

1241
01:04:26,440 --> 01:04:28,800
- His vibe is super unique.
- His hips stood out.

1242
01:04:28,880 --> 01:04:30,760
And he knows what makes him stand out.

1243
01:04:30,840 --> 01:04:34,360
He brings that energy constantly,
from the first take to the last.

1244
01:04:34,440 --> 01:04:38,320
Pom is incredibly charming.

1245
01:04:38,400 --> 01:04:40,400
He knows exactly how to work the camera.

1246
01:04:40,480 --> 01:04:43,960
His movement and body control
really outshone the rest of his team.

1247
01:04:44,040 --> 01:04:47,240
Pom sets the standard.
Let's just call him the gold standard.

1248
01:04:47,320 --> 01:04:49,680
The mentor knows exactly
how these guys move.

1249
01:04:49,760 --> 01:04:50,840
Right.

1250
01:04:50,920 --> 01:04:53,600
And coaches them
on how to use their bodies.

1251
01:04:53,680 --> 01:04:55,440
He could explain it perfectly.

1252
01:04:55,520 --> 01:04:59,280
So the guys get the picture
and elevate their performance.

1253
01:04:59,360 --> 01:05:01,720
They get better with every single take.

1254
01:05:01,800 --> 01:05:03,560
That's the best part.

1255
01:05:03,640 --> 01:05:06,120
- Thank you.
- Let's move on to Mentor Mile's team.

1256
01:05:06,200 --> 01:05:07,560
First up, Peem.

1257
01:05:07,640 --> 01:05:11,360
Peem arguably had the best dance skills
out of anyone today.

1258
01:05:11,440 --> 01:05:15,400
He knows his body.
He has his own natural groove.

1259
01:05:15,480 --> 01:05:18,560
And he executed it perfectly,
just like in the master class.

1260
01:05:19,520 --> 01:05:23,520
If I had to critique anything,
it would be his facial expressions.

1261
01:05:23,600 --> 01:05:27,120
Just a little more emotion,
and he would be absolutely perfect.

1262
01:05:27,720 --> 01:05:29,960
Second is Manyoo.

1263
01:05:30,040 --> 01:05:32,760
He fell flat today
and faded into the background.

1264
01:05:32,840 --> 01:05:37,720
- Not just within his team, but overall.
- Right.

1265
01:05:37,800 --> 01:05:40,160
As for Gluf today…
Gluf has a massive advantage.

1266
01:05:40,240 --> 01:05:42,200
His vibe is just young and fresh.

1267
01:05:42,280 --> 01:05:43,520
He's vibrant and playful.

1268
01:05:43,600 --> 01:05:47,400
When he works the camera, he gives us
variety, mixing cheeky with cute.

1269
01:05:47,480 --> 01:05:50,760
All in all, it makes him
incredibly charming.

1270
01:05:50,840 --> 01:05:53,520
Why do I feel like Gluf
is an actual dancer?

1271
01:05:53,600 --> 01:05:56,040
Like a pro who just naturally
grooves to the beat.

1272
01:05:56,120 --> 01:06:00,120
I didn't expect him
to pop off like this today. Yes.

1273
01:06:00,200 --> 01:06:03,400
And I loved Mentor Mile's camera work.
The way he found angles…

1274
01:06:03,480 --> 01:06:05,120
Instead of shooting straight on,

1275
01:06:05,200 --> 01:06:07,800
he used dynamic angles
like a real music video.

1276
01:06:07,880 --> 01:06:10,160
So it didn't feel repetitive.

1277
01:06:10,240 --> 01:06:12,000
All right, that's two teams down.

1278
01:06:12,080 --> 01:06:14,720
Now for the final team.
Team Pancake-Ananda.

1279
01:06:14,800 --> 01:06:16,080
- Your thoughts?
- Right.

1280
01:06:16,160 --> 01:06:19,280
Kimhan has been incredibly consistent
since day one.

1281
01:06:19,360 --> 01:06:20,800
He's undeniably talented.

1282
01:06:20,880 --> 01:06:23,000
He has a natural talent to work with.

1283
01:06:23,080 --> 01:06:25,440
But he tries so hard to be perfect.

1284
01:06:25,520 --> 01:06:30,560
So there were moments where he slipped.
You could see the stress on his face.

1285
01:06:30,640 --> 01:06:32,400
- He was anxious.
- But he always…

1286
01:06:32,480 --> 01:06:34,960
He always pushes to do better
every single time.

1287
01:06:35,560 --> 01:06:37,400
His only flaw is his eyes.

1288
01:06:37,480 --> 01:06:39,480
- He looks stiff, right?
- It's so obvious.

1289
01:06:39,560 --> 01:06:42,040
- No matter how hard he tries to relax.
- Yes.

1290
01:06:42,120 --> 01:06:44,080
- I get that he's super determined.
- Yes.

1291
01:06:44,160 --> 01:06:46,760
- But sometimes…
- You see anxiety behind the ambition.

1292
01:06:46,840 --> 01:06:48,200
He should relax more.

1293
01:06:48,280 --> 01:06:49,200
Exactly.

1294
01:06:49,840 --> 01:06:54,200
I've told the boys from the start,
"Hey, making it this far is no joke."

1295
01:06:54,280 --> 01:06:57,120
The fact that you survived this long
proves you're good.

1296
01:06:57,200 --> 01:07:00,800
Everything from here on out is a bonus.
Enjoy it.

1297
01:07:00,880 --> 01:07:04,720
Have fun being in this together
and just create something amazing.

1298
01:07:05,960 --> 01:07:07,560
For those who want to be artists,

1299
01:07:07,640 --> 01:07:10,040
you never know
when your big break will come.

1300
01:07:10,120 --> 01:07:12,240
If you quit, it's truly over.

1301
01:07:12,320 --> 01:07:15,240
If you really love it, you'll never stop.
Believe in yourself.

1302
01:07:15,320 --> 01:07:18,000
The first battle
is conquering your own mind.

1303
01:07:18,080 --> 01:07:20,520
And just find joy in whatever you do.

1304
01:07:20,600 --> 01:07:24,160
And what does
today's campaign winner receive, Golf?

1305
01:07:24,240 --> 01:07:27,320
The winner of today's campaign
will receive a gift voucher

1306
01:07:27,400 --> 01:07:31,040
worth 20,000 baht for
a full styling session at TUR Hair Salon.

1307
01:07:31,120 --> 01:07:34,400
Plus, a one-year supply
of Clear products for the entire team.

1308
01:07:36,080 --> 01:07:37,760
- Does that include mentors?
- No.

1309
01:07:37,840 --> 01:07:39,840
- Actually, yes.
- Mentors included.

1310
01:07:39,920 --> 01:07:40,760
Mentors included.

1311
01:07:40,840 --> 01:07:41,960
Can I wash my hair now?

1312
01:07:43,320 --> 01:07:48,880
All right. Which team won
the "Up, Up, Clear Away" campaign?

1313
01:07:52,440 --> 01:07:55,920
We'll find out the results
during the selection for the Final Walk.

1314
01:07:56,000 --> 01:07:57,440
Kim wouldn't spill the tea.

1315
01:07:57,520 --> 01:07:58,600
Kim, you're so dead.

1316
01:07:59,800 --> 01:08:02,960
And that's a wrap
for the "Up, Up, Clear Away" campaign.

1317
01:08:03,040 --> 01:08:05,840
Right now, our judges
are going to tally up the scores.

1318
01:08:05,920 --> 01:08:07,480
We'll be back with the results.

1319
01:08:08,160 --> 01:08:11,200
I don't know the results,
but the boys gave it their all.

1320
01:08:11,280 --> 01:08:13,080
We might just get some good news.

1321
01:08:13,160 --> 01:08:16,120
I still can't see
who's going to the Final Walk.

1322
01:08:16,200 --> 01:08:18,439
I have no idea how I'm going to decide.

1323
01:08:19,439 --> 01:08:21,520
Somebody help me.

1324
01:08:21,600 --> 01:08:23,439
I just want to taste victory for once.

1325
01:08:23,520 --> 01:08:27,800
Even if I don't get to judge
in the Black Room, that's fine.

1326
01:08:27,880 --> 01:08:29,920
I just want a win,
so the boys can be proud.

1327
01:08:50,720 --> 01:08:52,080
What are you doing?

1328
01:08:52,160 --> 01:08:56,880
I just ordered a jacket this morning
to be delivered to <i>The Face </i>studio today.

1329
01:08:56,960 --> 01:08:59,640
Will it make it in time?
We're about to shoot.

1330
01:08:59,720 --> 01:09:03,040
It will. I ordered it this morning,
and it will be here soon.

1331
01:09:03,120 --> 01:09:04,120
<i>Shopee!</i>

1332
01:09:04,200 --> 01:09:05,560
See? There it is.

1333
01:09:06,240 --> 01:09:08,920
Thank you so much. Thanks.

1334
01:09:09,920 --> 01:09:12,120
Wow, you literally
just ordered this morning.

1335
01:09:12,200 --> 01:09:13,040
You got it?

1336
01:09:13,120 --> 01:09:14,920
Download the Shopee app, Kimhan.

1337
01:09:15,000 --> 01:09:17,920
Shopee has it all.
Fast, cheap, and guaranteed.

1338
01:09:30,399 --> 01:09:32,880
At first, the vibe seemed totally chill.

1339
01:09:32,960 --> 01:09:34,399
Felt safe.

1340
01:09:34,479 --> 01:09:38,920
It's sad. It's our last time in this room.
And our last time doing these interviews.

1341
01:09:39,560 --> 01:09:40,920
- Hello.
- Hello.

1342
01:09:41,000 --> 01:09:42,399
Welcome.

1343
01:09:42,479 --> 01:09:45,319
I'm incredibly proud
of you all for making it this far.

1344
01:09:45,399 --> 01:09:46,640
They made it here

1345
01:09:46,720 --> 01:09:50,800
because they took every critique
and just kept leveling up.

1346
01:09:52,800 --> 01:09:55,640
Welcome to the Final Four selection.

1347
01:09:55,720 --> 01:09:57,560
The road to the Final Walk.

1348
01:09:57,640 --> 01:09:59,000
Here are the rules for today.

1349
01:09:59,080 --> 01:10:00,680
Each mentor

1350
01:10:00,760 --> 01:10:04,320
can choose one contestant
for the Final Walk.

1351
01:10:04,400 --> 01:10:09,520
And the mentor who won the last campaign
gets to save one additional contestant.

1352
01:10:09,600 --> 01:10:10,720
So nerve-wracking.

1353
01:10:10,800 --> 01:10:13,800
I'm dying to know
who the other teams will pick.

1354
01:10:14,400 --> 01:10:17,680
I just want this journey to keep going.

1355
01:10:17,760 --> 01:10:18,840
I don't know.

1356
01:10:18,920 --> 01:10:21,960
I don't want to eliminate anyone.
It breaks my heart too much.

1357
01:10:22,560 --> 01:10:23,920
- Master Mentor Adam.
- Yes.

1358
01:10:24,000 --> 01:10:26,720
Master Mentor Adam,
anything you want to say to them?

1359
01:10:26,800 --> 01:10:30,600
Honestly, every single one
of you is incredible.

1360
01:10:30,680 --> 01:10:34,760
You've proven that your hard work,

1361
01:10:34,840 --> 01:10:36,000
your open minds,

1362
01:10:36,080 --> 01:10:38,960
and the raw energy
you bring every single time

1363
01:10:39,040 --> 01:10:40,360
are why you're here today.

1364
01:10:40,440 --> 01:10:42,280
Since day one,

1365
01:10:42,360 --> 01:10:45,440
we've seen you all
competing with yourselves.

1366
01:10:45,520 --> 01:10:47,000
And that is truly amazing.

1367
01:10:47,080 --> 01:10:48,320
Are you exhausted?

1368
01:10:48,920 --> 01:10:50,440
A little bit. Just a bit.

1369
01:10:50,520 --> 01:10:52,760
I have no idea who to pick today.

1370
01:10:52,840 --> 01:10:55,080
I feel for both Lincoln and Donut.

1371
01:10:55,160 --> 01:10:57,240
To be honest, it's totally unfair.

1372
01:10:57,320 --> 01:10:58,560
Tell you what.

1373
01:10:58,640 --> 01:11:01,000
If you win, you can bring them both back.

1374
01:11:02,400 --> 01:11:05,040
I'll allow it.
That's a Master Mentor for you.

1375
01:11:05,120 --> 01:11:09,400
Using the Master Mentor privilege
right there. That's a first in <i>The Face.</i>

1376
01:11:09,480 --> 01:11:10,680
Maybe I'd take that bet.

1377
01:11:10,760 --> 01:11:11,880
But you have to win.

1378
01:11:11,960 --> 01:11:13,640
- But I have to win?
- You have to win.

1379
01:11:14,880 --> 01:11:15,720
Shake on it.

1380
01:11:15,800 --> 01:11:17,480
Win, and you get both guys.

1381
01:11:17,560 --> 01:11:19,000
That would make history, no?

1382
01:11:20,040 --> 01:11:21,720
I wasn't nervous, but I am now.

1383
01:11:23,720 --> 01:11:25,280
It will be a new level of fun.

1384
01:11:25,360 --> 01:11:28,120
I have no objections.
Good for them if they win.

1385
01:11:28,200 --> 01:11:29,880
Over the past seven weeks,

1386
01:11:29,960 --> 01:11:32,400
you guys have been through a lot.

1387
01:11:32,480 --> 01:11:35,240
Mentor Mile, anything
you'd like to say to your boys?

1388
01:11:35,320 --> 01:11:36,880
The die-hard fans of <i>The Face</i>

1389
01:11:36,960 --> 01:11:39,280
expect me to do whatever it takes to win.

1390
01:11:39,360 --> 01:11:40,600
Winning is everything.

1391
01:11:40,680 --> 01:11:43,920
But for me, it's about making sure

1392
01:11:44,000 --> 01:11:45,760
the boys I drafted

1393
01:11:45,840 --> 01:11:48,000
get as much airtime as humanly possible.

1394
01:11:48,080 --> 01:11:51,000
They need to shine and show off
exactly what they can do.

1395
01:11:51,080 --> 01:11:52,680
So sweet. Do you love him?

1396
01:11:52,760 --> 01:11:54,040
Love him to death.

1397
01:11:54,120 --> 01:11:55,160
See?

1398
01:11:55,240 --> 01:11:56,240
Oh, wow.

1399
01:11:56,320 --> 01:11:58,280
We have to pick based on talent.

1400
01:11:58,360 --> 01:12:02,680
So maybe the guy with the most versatile
foundation is the right answer.

1401
01:12:02,760 --> 01:12:04,680
First off, thank you, guys.

1402
01:12:04,760 --> 01:12:08,600
Our team wouldn't be this tight-knit
if you didn't care for each other

1403
01:12:08,680 --> 01:12:10,360
and have each other's backs.

1404
01:12:10,440 --> 01:12:14,440
And thanks for making us
look like a real, solid team.

1405
01:12:14,520 --> 01:12:16,720
We've got three dishes ready to serve.

1406
01:12:16,800 --> 01:12:19,720
It just depends on
which flavor we want to present.

1407
01:12:19,800 --> 01:12:23,880
Look, I'm not trying to be dramatic.

1408
01:12:23,960 --> 01:12:26,840
Honestly, doing <i>The Face</i>
wasn't even on my radar.

1409
01:12:26,920 --> 01:12:29,120
I just didn't think I knew how to mentor.

1410
01:12:29,200 --> 01:12:32,880
I kept saying, "No, this isn't me.
They aren't my main priority."

1411
01:12:32,960 --> 01:12:36,640
But something changed. I don't even know
when they snuck into my heart.

1412
01:12:36,720 --> 01:12:38,840
Honestly, it's all because of you guys.

1413
01:12:38,920 --> 01:12:41,840
So I just want to thank all of you.

1414
01:12:41,920 --> 01:12:43,200
For being my inspiration.

1415
01:12:43,280 --> 01:12:45,200
I'm so glad I could inspire him.

1416
01:12:45,280 --> 01:12:47,800
His acting has always been
an inspiration to me.

1417
01:12:47,880 --> 01:12:52,200
Today, I'm giving all of you the floor
to speak from the heart to your mentors.

1418
01:12:52,280 --> 01:12:54,280
Let's start with Team Mentor Mile.

1419
01:12:54,360 --> 01:12:56,880
Peem, what do you
want to say to Mentor Mile?

1420
01:12:56,960 --> 01:12:58,600
I'll be completely raw here.

1421
01:12:58,680 --> 01:13:00,360
And just speak my truth.

1422
01:13:00,960 --> 01:13:02,200
Before I joined <i>The Face</i>,

1423
01:13:02,280 --> 01:13:06,120
people everywhere told me I was talented.

1424
01:13:06,200 --> 01:13:09,360
But at the end of the day,
I never truly stood out.

1425
01:13:09,440 --> 01:13:11,440
Taking the leap to do this show

1426
01:13:11,520 --> 01:13:14,760
helped me finally figure out who I am.

1427
01:13:15,360 --> 01:13:21,600
I tried to learn from my past mistakes.

1428
01:13:21,680 --> 01:13:25,080
And just do my absolute best.
Thanks for being so patient with me.

1429
01:13:25,160 --> 01:13:28,400
And helping me on and off camera.

1430
01:13:28,480 --> 01:13:31,040
Whether I make the Final Walk or not,

1431
01:13:31,120 --> 01:13:33,560
I'm going to keep leveling up.

1432
01:13:33,640 --> 01:13:35,480
I love you. I love you so much, Mile.

1433
01:13:35,560 --> 01:13:37,080
I already knew what he'd say.

1434
01:13:37,160 --> 01:13:38,560
I knew exactly how he felt.

1435
01:13:38,640 --> 01:13:41,120
That was so touching. Man, he's crying.

1436
01:13:41,200 --> 01:13:42,320
Don't tease me.

1437
01:13:43,520 --> 01:13:45,320
Next up, Gluf.

1438
01:13:45,400 --> 01:13:50,320
My journey on <i>The Face</i>
has been a total rollercoaster.

1439
01:13:50,400 --> 01:13:54,120
My main goal here was
to step out of my comfort zone.

1440
01:13:54,200 --> 01:13:56,680
I had to be fearless and give it my all.

1441
01:13:56,760 --> 01:14:00,680
I'm so proud I survived every trip
to the Black Room.

1442
01:14:00,760 --> 01:14:05,280
If you pick me,
I swear I won't let anyone down.

1443
01:14:05,360 --> 01:14:08,160
I'll represent you guys
and make you proud.

1444
01:14:08,240 --> 01:14:09,560
I gave it my all.

1445
01:14:09,640 --> 01:14:12,960
Expressing my feelings is harder
than being in the Black Room.

1446
01:14:13,040 --> 01:14:15,560
And the final member of the team, Manyoo.

1447
01:14:15,640 --> 01:14:19,520
The day you picked me,
I didn't even know my own worth.

1448
01:14:19,600 --> 01:14:23,680
But over time,
I started to believe in myself more.

1449
01:14:23,760 --> 01:14:26,960
We lost a lot,
but we never stopped trying.

1450
01:14:27,040 --> 01:14:29,960
I wanted that moment of jumping
and screaming, "We won!"

1451
01:14:30,560 --> 01:14:33,280
I'm really sorry to Mile for that.

1452
01:14:33,360 --> 01:14:39,320
And thank you to all the mentors
for shaping me, on and off camera.

1453
01:14:39,400 --> 01:14:41,960
If Manyoo moves forward,
that'd be a huge shock.

1454
01:14:42,040 --> 01:14:45,680
I'm kind of rooting for him, honestly.
I'm secretly proud of his progress.

1455
01:14:45,760 --> 01:14:47,840
Huge thanks to all my friends.

1456
01:14:49,000 --> 01:14:51,720
In the last master class and campaign,

1457
01:14:51,800 --> 01:14:54,320
you guys fought hard for us
until the very end.

1458
01:14:54,920 --> 01:14:56,920
And a massive thank you to Mile.

1459
01:14:57,000 --> 01:15:00,800
Thanks for picking me
and for being so patient with all of us.

1460
01:15:00,880 --> 01:15:02,840
I want the Final Walk so badly.

1461
01:15:02,920 --> 01:15:04,360
If it's not me, that's okay.

1462
01:15:04,440 --> 01:15:07,800
But if it is, I'm ready to fight
for all of my friends.

1463
01:15:07,880 --> 01:15:09,560
The time has come.

1464
01:15:09,640 --> 01:15:12,280
Who will Mentor Mile pick
for the Final Walk?

1465
01:15:12,360 --> 01:15:13,960
Stop chasing what isn't you.

1466
01:15:14,040 --> 01:15:16,600
Your best asset is yourself.

1467
01:15:16,680 --> 01:15:20,760
Your authenticity and natural vibe
can't be faked.

1468
01:15:20,840 --> 01:15:25,080
Peem, you give your all to everything.
You love diving out of your comfort zone.

1469
01:15:25,160 --> 01:15:29,040
Finding that balance has made you
even more charming.

1470
01:15:29,120 --> 01:15:30,760
You've become your best self.

1471
01:15:30,840 --> 01:15:33,120
Just hearing that is so reassuring.

1472
01:15:33,200 --> 01:15:35,560
Gluf was like a gift
from the Master Mentor.

1473
01:15:35,640 --> 01:15:40,200
But it was your own grit
that got you here.

1474
01:15:40,280 --> 01:15:41,760
You killed it yesterday.

1475
01:15:41,840 --> 01:15:44,000
I'm so anxious to see what happens today.

1476
01:15:44,080 --> 01:15:47,160
As for Manyoo, I see your dedication.

1477
01:15:47,240 --> 01:15:50,960
I have absolutely no regrets drafting you.

1478
01:15:51,040 --> 01:15:53,240
Discipline is crucial, and you have it.

1479
01:15:53,320 --> 01:15:55,440
He's incredibly focused.

1480
01:15:55,520 --> 01:15:59,920
And he brings a completely
unique energy to the group.

1481
01:16:00,000 --> 01:16:05,680
I have to choose based on who can deliver
the best performance for what's left.

1482
01:16:06,280 --> 01:16:08,720
I love and respect all of you guys.

1483
01:16:08,800 --> 01:16:10,760
Exactly as you are.

1484
01:16:10,840 --> 01:16:13,320
Having to pick just one is heartbreaking.

1485
01:16:13,400 --> 01:16:15,280
Even a logical person has a heart.

1486
01:16:15,880 --> 01:16:16,960
Why am I so nervous?

1487
01:16:17,040 --> 01:16:21,440
If he's playing the game,
Peem is the most well-rounded choice.

1488
01:16:21,520 --> 01:16:23,560
But I have a gut feeling
he'll pick Manyoo.

1489
01:16:24,600 --> 01:16:25,480
Manyoo.

1490
01:16:27,120 --> 01:16:29,280
Manyoo, you are not my Final Walk.

1491
01:16:31,880 --> 01:16:32,720
Peem.

1492
01:16:33,720 --> 01:16:35,200
Let's go to the Final Walk.

1493
01:16:35,280 --> 01:16:37,600
Huge congratulations to Peem.

1494
01:16:39,200 --> 01:16:41,600
It sucks that Manyoo's journey
was cut short.

1495
01:16:41,680 --> 01:16:43,400
If he just had a little more time…

1496
01:16:43,480 --> 01:16:44,760
I know he'd have gone far.

1497
01:16:46,160 --> 01:16:47,760
So happy for you, man.

1498
01:16:49,320 --> 01:16:52,280
Peem just has a stronger skill set
than the rest.

1499
01:16:52,360 --> 01:16:55,800
All he needs now
is the right mindset and balance.

1500
01:16:55,880 --> 01:16:58,760
And that's much faster to teach
than raw skills.

1501
01:17:00,400 --> 01:17:02,160
I'm thrilled.

1502
01:17:02,240 --> 01:17:04,840
And I want to put on
the most epic show possible.

1503
01:17:04,920 --> 01:17:07,200
If I have to jump off
a building, I'll do it.

1504
01:17:07,280 --> 01:17:09,800
Let's move right along to Team Mentor Off.

1505
01:17:09,880 --> 01:17:11,120
Bonus.

1506
01:17:11,200 --> 01:17:13,880
If this is a personality contest,
he'd win hands down.

1507
01:17:13,960 --> 01:17:14,960
He's a charming guy.

1508
01:17:15,040 --> 01:17:18,240
Coming into this with a friend…

1509
01:17:18,320 --> 01:17:20,760
I thought just being myself
would be enough.

1510
01:17:20,840 --> 01:17:22,960
But then the first campaign hit.

1511
01:17:23,040 --> 01:17:25,640
Total disaster.
I felt like complete garbage.

1512
01:17:25,720 --> 01:17:29,840
After that shoot,
I promised to give 100 percent.

1513
01:17:29,920 --> 01:17:31,720
Every single second I'm on camera,

1514
01:17:31,800 --> 01:17:32,880
I'm going to bring it.

1515
01:17:32,960 --> 01:17:35,200
I watched every season of <i>The Face</i>.

1516
01:17:35,280 --> 01:17:38,360
Every campaign, master class,
my heart was pounding.

1517
01:17:38,440 --> 01:17:41,560
I had to nail it.
I crave that adrenaline rush.

1518
01:17:41,640 --> 01:17:45,600
Being here has taught me
so much about myself.

1519
01:17:45,680 --> 01:17:47,440
We all know what Off is thinking.

1520
01:17:47,520 --> 01:17:49,800
And I know I'm not going
to the Final Walk.

1521
01:17:49,880 --> 01:17:51,640
Off shouldn't choose me, honestly.

1522
01:17:51,720 --> 01:17:53,880
No hard feelings. Just man to man.

1523
01:17:54,480 --> 01:17:55,600
Thanks, Off.

1524
01:17:55,680 --> 01:17:59,000
Since day one, when I got cut,

1525
01:17:59,080 --> 01:18:00,520
and earned my way back,

1526
01:18:01,120 --> 01:18:03,240
thanks for seeing my potential.

1527
01:18:03,320 --> 01:18:06,440
You taught me everything,
from the first episode until now.

1528
01:18:06,520 --> 01:18:08,080
I fight for the team. For you.

1529
01:18:08,160 --> 01:18:12,280
I fight for everyone who has supported me.

1530
01:18:12,360 --> 01:18:14,360
I'm incredibly proud of myself.

1531
01:18:14,440 --> 01:18:18,120
Whether Rome or Bonus makes it,

1532
01:18:18,200 --> 01:18:22,280
I know our team has what it takes
to slay the Final Walk.

1533
01:18:22,360 --> 01:18:25,240
I might be babbling a bit

1534
01:18:25,320 --> 01:18:27,760
because I'm nervous. Plus, earlier, I…

1535
01:18:27,840 --> 01:18:30,320
I cried my eyes out.
Trying to hold it together.

1536
01:18:30,400 --> 01:18:33,200
Never thought we would make it this far.

1537
01:18:33,280 --> 01:18:35,320
And we snatched so many wins.

1538
01:18:35,400 --> 01:18:37,840
Rome, anything you want
to say to Mentor Off?

1539
01:18:37,920 --> 01:18:42,360
I joined this show to challenge myself.

1540
01:18:42,440 --> 01:18:47,640
And I did grow.
At first, I was killing it and having fun.

1541
01:18:47,720 --> 01:18:49,800
But as the campaigns went on,

1542
01:18:49,880 --> 01:18:51,800
the anxiety hit me.

1543
01:18:51,880 --> 01:18:53,920
They were totally new to me.

1544
01:18:54,000 --> 01:18:56,080
I had never done
anything like that before.

1545
01:18:56,160 --> 01:18:58,440
Off brought out my true self.

1546
01:18:58,520 --> 01:19:03,280
And we fought our way to the very end.

1547
01:19:04,080 --> 01:19:06,000
As for the Final Walk,

1548
01:19:06,080 --> 01:19:09,240
if you pick me, I'll give it my all.

1549
01:19:09,840 --> 01:19:13,560
I know I have what it takes
to crush the other teams.

1550
01:19:13,640 --> 01:19:17,600
Bonus, Pom basically gave up.
Like they don't even want the Final Walk.

1551
01:19:17,680 --> 01:19:19,960
Rome is the only one
trying to prove himself.

1552
01:19:20,040 --> 01:19:23,360
Honestly, everyone wants the Final Walk.
We're so close.

1553
01:19:23,440 --> 01:19:24,480
Of course, I want it.

1554
01:19:24,560 --> 01:19:26,280
Just going to do my absolute best.

1555
01:19:26,960 --> 01:19:29,080
My first day as a mentor,

1556
01:19:29,160 --> 01:19:32,320
I couldn't picture myself doing this.
I had my doubts.

1557
01:19:33,040 --> 01:19:37,000
But you guys made me a true mentor.

1558
01:19:37,080 --> 01:19:40,440
Bonus, you dove headfirst into everything.

1559
01:19:40,520 --> 01:19:42,680
You started from the bottom,

1560
01:19:42,760 --> 01:19:44,840
and I've watched you evolve.

1561
01:19:44,920 --> 01:19:48,080
I'm so glad we met.

1562
01:19:48,160 --> 01:19:49,040
Thanks, man.

1563
01:19:49,120 --> 01:19:51,680
I have zero regrets picking Bonus.

1564
01:19:51,760 --> 01:19:55,040
He's the poster boy
for pure hustle and grit.

1565
01:19:55,640 --> 01:19:58,040
First off, thanks to the Master Mentor

1566
01:19:58,120 --> 01:20:00,040
for handing Pom to me.

1567
01:20:00,120 --> 01:20:03,800
Pom literally rose from the ashes.

1568
01:20:03,880 --> 01:20:06,320
He's back from the dead,
with his back against the wall.

1569
01:20:06,400 --> 01:20:07,720
He can't afford to lose.

1570
01:20:07,800 --> 01:20:11,280
Our team is full of hardcore fighters.
We hustle hard.

1571
01:20:11,360 --> 01:20:14,520
I'm incredibly proud to have Pom.

1572
01:20:14,600 --> 01:20:17,320
Pom is the total package.
He's serving every flavor.

1573
01:20:17,400 --> 01:20:18,400
He's a whole meal.

1574
01:20:18,480 --> 01:20:21,680
Rome, you're so genuine today.
It's the most you've ever spoken.

1575
01:20:21,760 --> 01:20:23,040
You've got the goods.

1576
01:20:23,120 --> 01:20:25,200
You're 190cm tall with a gorgeous face.

1577
01:20:25,280 --> 01:20:26,960
So own it. Be confident.

1578
01:20:27,040 --> 01:20:31,280
I feel like Rome is still holding back.
He hasn't unleashed his full potential.

1579
01:20:31,360 --> 01:20:34,400
Based on the talent show,
I think it's obvious to everyone.

1580
01:20:35,000 --> 01:20:38,760
Pom was the most well-rounded performer.

1581
01:20:39,480 --> 01:20:41,560
Let's go. Keep it moving.

1582
01:20:41,640 --> 01:20:43,920
Honestly, Pom is a wild card.

1583
01:20:44,000 --> 01:20:47,160
I didn't see that coming.
I thought he was going to pick Rome.

1584
01:20:47,240 --> 01:20:49,640
This is the reward for pure hustle.

1585
01:20:49,720 --> 01:20:52,000
The ultimate reward for a fighter.

1586
01:20:52,960 --> 01:20:55,440
But hey, that might just work
in our favor, right?

1587
01:20:59,200 --> 01:21:03,640
I came here to fight for my team.

1588
01:21:03,720 --> 01:21:05,160
For Off. For everyone.

1589
01:21:06,840 --> 01:21:10,640
Honestly, I feel so relieved today.
It has been so rewarding.

1590
01:21:10,720 --> 01:21:14,800
I'm just incredibly proud
I made it this far.

1591
01:21:14,880 --> 01:21:17,360
I can confidently say I'm tough as nails.

1592
01:21:18,160 --> 01:21:19,920
All right, that's two teams down.

1593
01:21:20,000 --> 01:21:23,080
Now for our final team,
Team Pancake and Ananda.

1594
01:21:23,160 --> 01:21:25,560
You're down to just one member.

1595
01:21:25,640 --> 01:21:29,840
Which means, naturally, Kimhan
automatically advances to the Final Walk.

1596
01:21:29,920 --> 01:21:33,680
Kimhan, any words for your mentors?

1597
01:21:33,760 --> 01:21:36,800
Today, you guys get to see
a different side of me.

1598
01:21:36,880 --> 01:21:39,360
I used to be a guy with zero dreams.

1599
01:21:39,440 --> 01:21:42,200
Completely lost.
I never did anything for myself.

1600
01:21:42,800 --> 01:21:46,600
My only goal was to make
my grandparents proud.

1601
01:21:47,680 --> 01:21:50,360
But entering <i>The Face</i>?
That feels too small now.

1602
01:21:50,440 --> 01:21:51,640
I'm setting the bar higher.

1603
01:21:52,600 --> 01:21:57,240
I kept looking for a reason
to push forward.

1604
01:21:57,840 --> 01:22:00,560
And it was right in front of me.
It was all of you.

1605
01:22:01,240 --> 01:22:03,640
Seeing the guys show up,

1606
01:22:03,720 --> 01:22:05,800
seeing you all arrive so early…

1607
01:22:08,000 --> 01:22:10,200
You guys are my driving force.

1608
01:22:10,800 --> 01:22:14,720
No matter how exhausted I get,
I know you guys are working twice as hard.

1609
01:22:14,800 --> 01:22:19,480
That drive makes me want
to give it all back to you.

1610
01:22:19,560 --> 01:22:21,360
And to the fans watching too.

1611
01:22:21,960 --> 01:22:25,160
That's why I keep my head down
and grind through it all.

1612
01:22:25,240 --> 01:22:28,160
This show is my absolute
number one priority.

1613
01:22:28,240 --> 01:22:30,080
It has given me more than I imagined.

1614
01:22:30,160 --> 01:22:32,320
It has completely blown my mind.

1615
01:22:32,400 --> 01:22:33,880
As for the Final Walk,

1616
01:22:33,960 --> 01:22:36,440
I'll prove to you that picking me
wasn't a mistake.

1617
01:22:36,520 --> 01:22:38,320
The best thing about him

1618
01:22:38,400 --> 01:22:39,640
is how receptive he is.

1619
01:22:39,720 --> 01:22:40,640
He's an open book.

1620
01:22:40,720 --> 01:22:42,240
He's incredibly versatile.

1621
01:22:42,840 --> 01:22:45,080
You deserve this, man. Seriously.

1622
01:22:45,160 --> 01:22:47,160
Come here, give me a hug.

1623
01:22:47,240 --> 01:22:48,880
He's totally sincere.

1624
01:22:48,960 --> 01:22:51,400
What you see is exactly what you get.

1625
01:22:51,480 --> 01:22:53,520
He fights to evolve.

1626
01:22:53,600 --> 01:22:57,680
Mentor Pancake, is there anything
you want to say to Kimhan?

1627
01:22:57,760 --> 01:23:00,920
On day one, Kimhan was practically
on the chopping block.

1628
01:23:01,000 --> 01:23:03,760
But we took a leap of faith with him.

1629
01:23:03,840 --> 01:23:05,520
And he proved us right.

1630
01:23:05,600 --> 01:23:09,440
Overcoming obstacles you never saw coming
is what truly matters.

1631
01:23:09,520 --> 01:23:13,200
You're talented,
and you hustle every single time.

1632
01:23:13,280 --> 01:23:15,080
I think you've killed it all season.

1633
01:23:15,160 --> 01:23:18,560
Winning or losing isn't as important
as giving it your absolute all.

1634
01:23:18,640 --> 01:23:21,480
Thank God I didn't have to choose.
Thank God!

1635
01:23:21,560 --> 01:23:23,760
We went from hating him to loving him.

1636
01:23:23,840 --> 01:23:27,040
I just handed you the Final Walk.
If you win, drag me up with you.

1637
01:23:27,120 --> 01:23:29,400
But please hang on for a second.

1638
01:23:29,480 --> 01:23:32,720
Today, each team will select one member.

1639
01:23:32,800 --> 01:23:37,240
And one extra spot goes to the winner
of the last campaign.

1640
01:23:37,320 --> 01:23:42,080
Master Mentor Adam already told
Team Pancake-Ananda

1641
01:23:42,160 --> 01:23:44,080
that if your team wins,

1642
01:23:44,160 --> 01:23:48,240
you can bring back an eliminated member

1643
01:23:48,320 --> 01:23:49,840
to compete in the Final Walk.

1644
01:23:49,920 --> 01:23:52,480
My team gets to bring one person back.

1645
01:23:52,560 --> 01:23:53,840
I want this win so bad.

1646
01:23:53,920 --> 01:23:55,960
Let's find out the results.

1647
01:23:56,040 --> 01:23:59,520
Who won the "Up, Up, Clear Away" campaign?

1648
01:23:59,600 --> 01:24:03,080
Out of all seven guys,
everyone had their own unique charm.

1649
01:24:03,160 --> 01:24:05,720
It was hard to tell
who nailed the concept.

1650
01:24:05,800 --> 01:24:07,920
Looking at the MV dance as a whole,

1651
01:24:08,000 --> 01:24:11,960
Gluf was the one
who really shone in the final cut.

1652
01:24:13,000 --> 01:24:17,600
And the absolute best performer
in the "Is that CLEAR?" MV campaign,

1653
01:24:17,680 --> 01:24:20,040
leading their team to victory, is…

1654
01:24:20,760 --> 01:24:22,440
At first, I felt like

1655
01:24:22,520 --> 01:24:24,760
we had a huge chance of winning.

1656
01:24:24,840 --> 01:24:28,160
My heart was pounding out of my chest.
I was on the verge of tears.

1657
01:24:35,360 --> 01:24:40,120
And the absolute best performer
in the "Is that CLEAR?" MV campaign,

1658
01:24:40,200 --> 01:24:42,400
leading their team to victory, is…

1659
01:24:43,040 --> 01:24:43,880
At first,

1660
01:24:43,960 --> 01:24:47,120
I felt like we had a huge chance
of winning.

1661
01:24:47,200 --> 01:24:50,520
My heart was pounding out of my chest.
I was on the verge of tears.

1662
01:24:54,880 --> 01:24:56,480
Gluf from Team Mile.

1663
01:24:56,560 --> 01:25:00,280
- Oh, wow.
- Oh, wow.

1664
01:25:00,360 --> 01:25:01,600
I won the campaign.

1665
01:25:01,680 --> 01:25:03,920
Team Mile wins.

1666
01:25:04,000 --> 01:25:07,240
This win is a huge stepping stone for you.

1667
01:25:07,320 --> 01:25:09,920
Congratulations to Gluf and Mentor Mile.

1668
01:25:10,000 --> 01:25:13,000
Talk about a plot twist.
He dodged elimination so many times.

1669
01:25:13,080 --> 01:25:15,040
Wow, reality is crazier than fiction.

1670
01:25:15,120 --> 01:25:17,920
What was the point of my team's
and Off's wins?

1671
01:25:18,000 --> 01:25:19,960
Spill it, what amulet are you wearing?

1672
01:25:22,240 --> 01:25:24,400
I have it under my tongue. I can't say.

1673
01:25:24,480 --> 01:25:27,280
Mentor Mile, you should thank me
for saving him that day.

1674
01:25:27,360 --> 01:25:28,640
Thank you, Pancake.

1675
01:25:28,720 --> 01:25:32,560
Pancake has claimed credit
for Gluf like three times now.

1676
01:25:32,640 --> 01:25:34,240
Let's just blame it on her age.

1677
01:25:34,320 --> 01:25:36,240
That means, Mentor Mile,

1678
01:25:36,320 --> 01:25:40,720
you can choose one more member
for the Final Walk.

1679
01:25:41,880 --> 01:25:44,640
Gluf, what do you think?
Manyoo, what do you think?

1680
01:25:44,720 --> 01:25:46,880
Can you just decide, Mile?

1681
01:25:48,120 --> 01:25:49,560
I want Mentor Mile to choose.

1682
01:25:49,640 --> 01:25:52,480
Manyoo wants you to pick me,
and I want you to pick him.

1683
01:25:52,560 --> 01:25:55,520
It would be way too cruel
not to give it to Gluf.

1684
01:25:57,520 --> 01:25:58,880
Bonus.

1685
01:25:59,560 --> 01:26:02,280
Stay out of this.
Seriously, stay out of it.

1686
01:26:02,360 --> 01:26:06,000
I know you want to joke around,
but the vibe is pretty tense right now.

1687
01:26:06,080 --> 01:26:07,160
It's a serious moment.

1688
01:26:07,240 --> 01:26:09,120
Look…

1689
01:26:09,200 --> 01:26:11,520
The same rule applies.
Based on performance.

1690
01:26:12,120 --> 01:26:14,960
Gluf. It's you.
You're going to the Final Walk with me.

1691
01:26:15,040 --> 01:26:17,440
Congratulations, Gluf.

1692
01:26:18,560 --> 01:26:21,960
Gluf went from having zero chance
to making the Final Walk.

1693
01:26:22,040 --> 01:26:26,360
All right, Gluf and Kimhan,
please wait in the living room.

1694
01:26:26,440 --> 01:26:27,760
You've got nine lives, man.

1695
01:26:27,840 --> 01:26:29,240
So happy for Gluf.

1696
01:26:34,360 --> 01:26:36,840
This was the ultimate
emotional rollercoaster.

1697
01:26:36,920 --> 01:26:39,600
- We actually won?
- We won. We won the damn campaign.

1698
01:26:39,680 --> 01:26:41,760
Team Mile is unstoppable right now.

1699
01:26:41,840 --> 01:26:44,160
Next episode is probably
an acting challenge.

1700
01:26:44,240 --> 01:26:47,280
We're going to go all out and crush it.

1701
01:26:47,360 --> 01:26:50,680
I'm so ready. I just want to compete
and hit that Final Walk.

1702
01:26:50,760 --> 01:26:52,440
Don't talk about competing with me.

1703
01:26:52,520 --> 01:26:53,760
Practice the tagline first.

1704
01:26:53,840 --> 01:26:56,120
I don't even see them as rivals.

1705
01:26:56,200 --> 01:26:58,440
I've got enough on my own plate right now.

1706
01:26:58,520 --> 01:27:00,320
And to the rest of you guys,

1707
01:27:00,400 --> 01:27:03,000
I'm sorry. You are not The Face.

1708
01:27:03,080 --> 01:27:06,320
If there's one thing I want to say
about missing the Final Walk,

1709
01:27:06,400 --> 01:27:09,600
<i>it is that The Face </i>has been
the best experience of my entire life.

1710
01:27:09,680 --> 01:27:12,200
This is the perfect ending for me.

1711
01:27:12,280 --> 01:27:15,760
I'll take everything I've learned
into whatever comes next.

1712
01:27:16,520 --> 01:27:20,600
I just spoke my truth
and let it all come from the heart.

1713
01:27:20,680 --> 01:27:22,760
I have zero regrets.

1714
01:27:22,840 --> 01:27:25,680
The best part is the guys.

1715
01:27:25,760 --> 01:27:27,720
I've fully unlocked my true self.

1716
01:27:27,800 --> 01:27:29,760
And it's just been a blast.

1717
01:27:29,840 --> 01:27:31,800
At least we got to share this journey.

1718
01:27:31,880 --> 01:27:35,360
It has been an incredibly special chapter.

1719
01:27:35,440 --> 01:27:38,840
Today, I just want to thank our mentors
and Master Mentors.

1720
01:27:38,920 --> 01:27:40,480
Thank you so much.

1721
01:27:41,720 --> 01:27:46,240
Gluf and Pom weren't even picked at first.
Huge plot twist.

1722
01:27:46,320 --> 01:27:48,200
Go count my wins.

1723
01:27:48,280 --> 01:27:51,480
Gluf is bringing that lucky energy
to me and the whole team.

1724
01:27:51,560 --> 01:27:53,640
We don't do flukes. We make magic.

1725
01:27:53,720 --> 01:27:55,000
Keep the trophy warm for me.

1726
01:27:55,080 --> 01:27:56,920
Based on my track record,

1727
01:27:57,000 --> 01:28:00,160
I'm 200 percent sure
Kimhan is taking the crown.

1728
01:28:03,760 --> 01:28:05,360
Drama is preferable.

1729
01:28:05,440 --> 01:28:06,760
Look, you can rest easy.

